title: blue devil salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in a 2-quart dish.
Add pie filling and pineapple.
Chill until firm.

title: maxie's homemade milk bones
directions: Combine flour, milk, salt, garlic and shortening together like a pie crust dough, then add remaining ingredients.
Roll out dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Use milk bone shaped cookie cutter or any other shape you desire.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen large sized dog milk bones.

title: florentine sauerkraut casserole
directions: In a skillet, cook sausage and onion with olive oil until brown and onion is tender.
Drain.

title: cheese coins
directions: Mix and knead.
Shape into a long log.
Wrap and chill.
Cut into 1/4-inch coins.
Place onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: fried rice
directions: Fry bacon in pan; remove.
Place onions and green peppers in pan and cook until tender.
Remove.
Beat 3 eggs and scramble. Cook until done.
Crumble bacon; add to cooked eggs, then add onions, green peppers, rice and chicken back in same pan.
Season to taste with soy sauce.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl with an electric mixer. No sifting needed. Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: goey butter bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: easy fried chicken
directions: Cut chicken into pieces.
Mix flour, salt, paprika and pepper. Coat chicken with flour mixture.

title: chewy chocolate chip cookies(low calorie)
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat sugar, flour, baking powder and egg whites until well combined.
Add vanilla.
Stir in chocolate chips and walnuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet coated with nonstick cooking spray and dusted with flour.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Yields 36 cookies.

title: hawaiian kabobs
directions: Drain pineapple, reserve 1/2 cup juice.
Place pineapple chunks and all vegetables in a large bowl; set aside.
In saucepan, combine reserved pineapple juice, soy sauce, olive oil, brown sugar and spices.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, simmer uncovered for 5 minutes.
Pour over pineapple and vegetables.
Add meat, refrigerate at least 1 hour; stir occasionally.
Alternate pineapple, meat and vegetables onto skewers.
Grill about 20 minutes, turning and basting with juices of marinade a few times. Serve over cooked rice.

title: microwave peanut butter roll
directions: Combine white sugar, syrup, water and salt in glass casserole. Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Stir.
Place bowl back in microwave for 10 minutes on High.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar in mixer bowl until stiff peaks form.
Pour hot syrup over egg whites, beating constantly at high speed.
Add vanilla.
Beat for 4 to 5 minutes or until mixture holds its shape and starts to lose its gloss.
Put confectioners sugar on waxed paper, work into cooked mixture.
Roll out, spread with peanut butter.
Roll up jelly roll fashion.
Slice and place in container.

title: skillet corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spread iron skillet evenly and on sides with Crisco.
Mix ingredients well and pour into skillet.
Bake approximately 30 minutes or until brown.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together potatoes, white sugar, eggs, vanilla and 1 1/2 sticks melted oleo.
Bake in greased casserole dish for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecued pork
directions: Cut meat into 1/2 to 3/4-inch strips.
Combine garlic, ginger root, sugar, salt, sherry, soy sauce, honey, five spice and food coloring.
Pour over meat; marinate for 1 hour.
Remove meat from marinade and roast in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours, basting frequently with the marinade and drippings.

title: corn bread (plain)
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Pour into a well-oiled 8-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until well done.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Tear lettuce into bite size pieces.
Sprinkle onions and bits of bacon over top.
Mix together remaining ingredients in a 2 cup measuring cup.
Microwave 2 minutes or until bubbly.
Pour over lettuce.
Serve immediately.

title: sopaipilla(puffy pillows of bread)
directions: Mix like biscuit dough and roll out 1/8-inch thick.
Cut in 3-inch triangles or squares; drop in deep fat and fry until golden brown.
Turn with spatula to brown other side.
Serve warm with warmed honey.
Good served with any Mexican dish.

title: sausage and pepper casserole
directions: Fry
sausage
and
drain.
Add	mushrooms, tomatoes and peppers
in
frying pan for 10 minutes.
Then put in casserole and top
with grated cheese and bread crumbs.	Cover and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: stir-fried broccoli
directions: Wash broccoli.
Cut flowerets from stems and set aside.
Peel stems and cut diagonally into 1/4-inch pieces.
Heat chicken broth and sesame oil in wok or heavy skillet.
Stir-fry stems for 2 minutes.
Add flowerets and stir-fry 2 more minutes.
Add cornstarch dissolved in 2 tablespoons water and toss quickly to coat and glaze broccoli.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Serves 4 as side dish or add to pasta.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients through cream cheese.
Just before it is set, add the pineapple, marshmallows and nuts.
Pour into 6-cup ring mold and chill until firm.

title: party pizza
directions: Mix ingredients together; spread on sliced French bread rolls or small rye bread rounds.
Broil until cheese is melted and browned.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: applesauce meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly; place in loaf pan.
Spread 2 tablespoons chili sauce over the top of meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat; bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
Drop from teaspoon on wax paper. Makes 36 cookies.

title: punch
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: blueberry torte
directions: First Layer: Mix flour, chopped nuts and oleo and spread in dish.
Cook about 30 minutes at 350° until light brown.

title: perfect white bread
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and let stand in a warm place until bubbling nicely.
In a large bowl, stir together 1/3 cup sugar, 2 1/2 cups water, 4 cups flour and 3/4 cup dried skim milk. Stir in the yeast mixture, beating well.
Cover the bowl and let stand in a warm place until the sponge is well risen and bubbly. Add 3 cups warm water, 5 teaspoons salt and 1/2 cup lard; beat well.
Stir in 8 cups of flour, mixing until the dough cleans the bowl.
Spread the remaining 2 cups of flour on the pastry board. Turn out the dough and knead well, using a little additional flour if necessary to make it smooth and satiny.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temperature until really soft. Peel cucumbers and onions; grate and drain well.
Add salt, cheese and mayonnaise.
Cream together until well blended.
This will make around 150 pinwheel or open-faced sandwiches.

title: devil's delight(for halloween)
directions: Mix cake mix, egg, water and butter.
Make "fingers" of dough about 3 inches long.

title: oysters supreme
directions: Cook chopped celery 10 minutes in boiling salted water; drain and set aside.
Make cream sauce of butter, flour, milk and seasonings.
Cook and stir constantly until very thick.
Add celery and eggs to cream sauce.
Place oysters in baking dish. Top with sauce.
Cover with crumbled toast crumbs; dot with butter.
Cook for 20 minutes at 375°.

title: old fashioned apple pudding
directions: Use an 8 x 8-inch ungreased pan.
Put the blended first 3 ingredients into pan.
Mix next 6 ingredients well and spread over the apple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until the apples are done.

title: caramels
directions: Put sugar, syrup and 1/2 cup cream into heavy bottom pan. Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to boil and boil to soft ball stage.
Stir gently to prevent burning (don't beat or will cause sugar to crystalize).

title: tuna log
directions: Stir softened cream cheese, tuna, onion together in a bowl; stir in a dash or two of lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce to taste. Put nuts and parsley on waxed paper. Form into a log over nuts and parsley. Roll up in waxed paper and chill until time to serve.

title: lasagna rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, combine Ricotta cheese, spinach, Mozzarella,
Parmesan and egg. Spread about 1/3 cup cheese mixture on each noodle.

Roll up lengthwise. Pour 1/2 cup pasta sauce into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Arrange lasagna rolls, seam side down, in the dish. Top with remaining sauce. Cover with foil and bake 35 minutes. Garnish as desired.

title: 24 hour vegetable salad
directions: In large bowl, combine 3 cups of lettuce.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and sugar.
Layer in order: eggs (salt lightly), peas, bacon, remaining 3 cups of lettuce, green onions and cheese. Spread mayonnaise over top. Sprinkle with paprika.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: pea picken cake
directions: Mix cake mix, mandarin oranges (juice and all), 3 eggs and oil in a mixing bowl.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour cake mixture in and bake at 350° about 35 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix lemon juice and milk.
Add instant topping, pineapple and nuts.
Pour into baked pie crusts.
Refrigerate until set.
Makes 2 pies.

title: perfect baked custard
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and salt in mixing bowl.
Beat just enough to
blend together.
Add hot milk slowly and mix well. Stir
in vanilla.
Strain.
Pour
into
quart shallow baking
pan or 1 1/2 quart deep casserole.
Place in a pan of hot
water. Bake
in
slow
oven until knife inserted halfway
between center and edge comes out clean.
For shallow pan,	allow 45 minutes.
For deep casserole, allow 60 minutes. Cool.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: homemade pretzels
directions: Grease a large baking sheet.
Stir together the all-purpose and whole wheat flours.
Measure 1 1/2 cups of the flour mixture into a mixing bowl.
Stir in the yeast.
Add the hot water, oil and honey.
Beat until smooth, about 2 minutes.
Add enough of the remaining flour to make a moderately stiff dough.
Knead 4 minutes or until smooth.
Let rise until double.
Cut into 12 pieces and roll each to a rope 15 inches long.
Shape into pretzel form. Brush with water and sprinkle very lightly with salt.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake in a 425° oven for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 12 pretzels.

title: green tomato bars
directions: Drain tomatoes on paper towel for 10 minutes. In a saucepan, combine tomatoes, 1 cup of brown sugar and the lemon juice. Simmer, uncovered, for 20 to 25 minutes or until thickened. Remove from the heat and stir in the extract. Set aside.

title: take-along cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, including juice from fruit cocktail.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2 cake pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Frost warm cake with Coconut Icing.

title: low-fat tuna salad with fresh dill
directions: Combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Serve on lettuce or pita bread.
Serves 2.

title: poppy seed bundt cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine cake and pudding mixes, water, oil and eggs. Beat on low speed until moistened. Beat on medium for 2 minutes. Stir in the poppy seeds. Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch fluted tube pan. Bake at 350° for 48 to 52 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan to a wire rack to cool completely. Dust with confectioners sugar. Yield: 12 to 15 servings.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Melt chocolate or white bark and peanut butter in microwave or double boiler. Stir often to mix.
Cool and bit and add all remaining ingredients.
Stir with wooden spoon.
Drop by spoonfuls.
Let set to cool and set.
Makes about 11 dozen.

title: chicken chow mein casserole
directions: Mix together in casserole dish. Cover. Cook 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: leeks cooked with onion
directions: Remove roots from leeks.
Wash and chop into small pieces. Saute onion slowly in oil, but do not brown.
Add leeks and cook only until tender.
Season.
Serve as a side dish.

title: impossible pie
directions: Combine in blender.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, nutmeg or both.
Let set for about 10 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook sweet potatoes, peel and mash.
Add all other ingredients and pour into an unbaked pie crust. Bake at 250° for about 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cream.
Bring to boil.
Lower heat and cook for 20 minutes.
Add peanut butter and butter.
Stir, while cooking, for 5 more minutes.
Remove from heat and stir for about ten minutes before pouring.
This makes a creamier fudge.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt margarine and add flour and milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Add salt and can of water, stirring constantly.
It will begin to thicken.
Keep stirring and add the cheese.
When the cheese is melted, it is ready.

title: fast fruit cobbler
directions: Cut margarine into small pieces.
Combine margarine, flour, sugar and milk.
Pour the mixture into a medium, round or rectangular Pyrex dish.
Lay the fruit evenly on top of the mixture.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sock-it-to-me cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and cake mix.
Add eggs and sour cream, mixing well.
Add nuts; mix and pour half of batter into a tube pan or loaf pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar and cinnamon over batter and pour remaining half over cake and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: stuffed roasted peppers(low-fat)
directions: Cut peppers in half; remove seeds.
Place in large baking dish, cut side down.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until skins begin to bubble and peppers are just tender.

title: cheese chicken
directions: Roll chicken in Bisquick and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix soup, water and dry onion soup mix; pour over chicken. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Remove from oven and sprinkle cheese over chicken.
Return to oven to melt cheese.

title: peaches in caramel creme
directions: In
heavy
quart
saucepan, bring sugar and water to boiling
over moderately high heat, stirring constantly, until sugar
is	dissolved.
Reduce
heat.
Keeping
mixture
at
a simmer, continue to cook without stirring until mixture begins to turn a dark golden color, about 18 to 20 minutes.

title: bay country crab soup
directions: Put first 7 ingredients in a large pan and simmer, covered, until meat is very tender, about 3 hours.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer, covered, until vegetables are done.
Makes about 5 quarts soup.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Pop popcorn in oil in a large covered pan over medium heat. Shake frequently. When popping stops, remove from heat. Put in a large bowl. Add a mixture of (well mixed and heat a little) Karo, sugar and salt. Pour over popped corn. Stir until corn is evenly coated. Butter your hands and form popcorn into balls. May have to gently squeeze to make stick together.

title: cucumber onion dip
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Chill.
Serve with fresh raw vegetables.

title: mile high lemon chiffon pie
directions: Mix and cook preceding ingredients, except pie crust, in a double boiler, stirring frequently until consistency of thick custard.
Soak 2 tablespoons unflavored gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water until dissolved.
Add to hot custard and cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Beat in 1 cup sugar gradually, then beat again.
Fold cooled custard into beaten egg whites.
Put in baked pie shell and chill 3 hours.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: cheesecake
directions: Beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually add sugar, lemon and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine all ingredients, pour in large baking dish and top with topping.

title: garlic chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces into a shallow baking pan, skin side up. Sprinkle all ingredients evenly over top. Cut lemon rind into pieces and arrange through out chicken. Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Remove foil and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: pizza burgers
directions: To make ahead and freeze, fry all together and let it get cold.
Then mix together 1 can tomato soup and 1 cup grated Mozzarella cheese.
Add to hamburger.
Mix and spread on buns. Then freeze until ready to use.
To heat, place under broiler until warm.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Beat yolks.
Add lemon juice and salt.
Cook in saucepan until thick; cool until just warm.
Mix in whipped cream; set aside.
In small mixing bowl, beat egg whites until stiff and add to mixture. Line an 8 x 8-inch pan with grahams.
Smooth mixture on top. Freeze.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayo, sugar
and
vinegar.
Pour
over broccoli and onions.
Marinate 24 hours. Stir in almonds and bacon prior to serving.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: In bottom of pan (greased and floured), put pecans and coconut. Mix cake according to directions on box.
Pour over pecans and coconut.
Mix oleo, cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Beat together.
May be heated to thin.
Pour mixture over cake mix. Bake according to directions on the cake mix box.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sesame puffs
directions: Combine flour, salt and garlic in a medium bowl.
Cut in butter with a pastry blender until crumbly.
Stir in sour cream lightly until pastry holds together and leaves the sides of the bowl.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Roll out dough on a lightly floured surface to a thickness of 1/4-inch.
Cut with cookie cutters in desired shapes. Lightly brush with water and sprinkle with seed.
Bake 15 minutes until lightly browned.
Store airtight.

title: old-fashioned apple pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt and flour in mixing bowl.
Add lemon juice and fruit.
Add cinnamon and mix thoroughly.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Top with butter.
Add top crust and bake at 450° for 20 minutes and then reduce heat to 375° and bake until golden brown.

title: no sugar diet cookies
directions: Mix oleo, sweetener, vanilla and egg.
Beat 2 minutes with electric beater on high.
Add flour, water, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Beat on low until blended.
Stir in raisins and pecans. Dough will be soft.
Drop by teaspoonful 2 inches apart on ungreased pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: crazy cracker cookies
directions: Place layer of foil in 11 x 16-inch pan.
Lay crackers over foil.
In saucepan, combine sugar and butter and bring to boil. Boil 3 minutes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients except sugar and vinegar.
Mix sugar and vinegar and stir into slaw.
(Will keep for several days.)

title: church windows
directions: Melt margarine and morsels in microwave.
Cool until slightly warm.
Put marshmallows in large bowl.
Pour chocolate mixture over marshmallows and toss until coated.
Sprinkle coconut on piece of wax paper.
Pour marshmallow mixture on coconut. Sprinkle additional coconut on top.
Roll in wax paper.
Chill and slice. Makes 3 logs.

title: green beans with sesame seed
directions: Cook green beans as directed on package; drain.
Cook remaining ingredients in saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly until golden brown.
Pour over green beans.
Serves 4.

title: fiery chicken casserole(1 hour total)
directions: Rinse chicken.
Pat dry.
Cut chicken into serving pieces. Peel and chop onion.
In a skillet, heat butter.
Add chicken pieces, a few at a time.
Saute until well browned on all sides. Add onion.
Saute a few more minutes.
Sprinkle with salt and paprika.
Sprinkle with flour.
Stir to combine.
Cover.
Cook over medium-low heat about 25 minutes, turning chicken pieces over from time to time.
Add creme fraiche or sour cream and chili peppers.
Blend well.
Cook for another 4 to 5 minutes.
Season to taste.
Sprinkle with chopped or sliced chives.
Serve.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Mix together and fry on lightly greased griddle.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cake: Preheat oven to 350°. Butter and dot with flour three 8-inch x 2-inch round cake pans. In bowl, mix flour, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda, nutmeg, salt and cloves. In bowl, beat eggs and sugar on low heat in oil, cream, vanilla, ginger and orange zest. Beat in flour mixture; add carrots and walnuts. Pour batter into pans. Bake until dark golden brown, 35 to 40 minutes. Let cool in pans on rack 20 minutes. Turn out and cool completely.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and butter.
Put on medium heat and cook until boils one minute.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, salt, peanut butter and oats.
Stir well.
Drop on wax paper with a spoon.

title: golden chicken nuggets
directions: Preheat oven to 400° Combine soup mix with breadcrumbs.
Dip chicken in soup mixture, coating well.
Place in lightly greased large shallow baking pan and drizzle with butter.
Bake turning once.
Bake for 10 minutes or until done.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In 9x13 in. baking pan, melt butter in oven.

Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over butter, pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs. Top with remaining ingredients in order listed; press down firmly with fork. Bake 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Chill if desired.
Cut into bars.
Store covered at room temperature. *Can substitute peanut butter chips or other flavored if desired.

title: bridge mix
directions: Mix flour, oleo and walnuts.
Spread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Mix together cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip and spread on crust.
Mix puddings with milk and spread on second layer.
Spread remaining 1/2 of large Cool Whip on top.

title: chocolate torte
directions: Mix and press in pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 375° and cool.

title: ozark pudding
directions: Beat egg and sugar together for a long time until smooth.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt; add to the egg mixture.
Add nuts, apples and vanilla.
Bake in a greased pie pan at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: 10,000 dollar pie
directions: Mix well and bake in two 9-inch pie shells.
Let cool.
Keep in fridge.

title: rum sauce
directions: Beat butter in small bowl on medium speed until creamy.
Beat in egg yolk. Add powdered sugar until fluffy. Add rum.
Stir in orange peel.
Beat until well blended. Cover and refrigerate. Yields 1 cup.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly with sugar and dash of salt.
Add corn syrup and melted butter.
Add pecan halves and mix.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until knife inserted to center comes out clean.

title: crackle lemon drop cookies
directions: Beat egg. Add Cool Whip. Add cake mix (this is very sticky). Drop by teaspoons into powdered sugar. Bake on greased cookie sheet approximately 10 minutes at 350°.

title: mary rose's french apple cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening and add egg and milk. Roll out as a pastry.
Fill in with apples.
Dot with butter (add raisins if you like).
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: peggy's persimmon pudding
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and beat.
Stir in pulp. Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk and vanilla to first mixture.
Pour into greased Pyrex dishes (one 9 x 13-inch and one 8 x 8-inch).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a graham cracker crust.

title: butter pecan bars
directions: In a bowl, combine brown sugar and eggs.
Blend in sugar, butter and vanilla.
Slowly add flour, beating well.
Add pecans. In a lightly greased pan, bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Use a toothpick to test for doneness.
Remove pan to a rack.
Cut into bars when almost cool.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: molded cranberry salad
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Let stand 2 or 3 hours.
Add Jell-O to hot water.
Stir in cranberry mixture.
Pour into mold. Chill to set.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as package says.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into lightly greased casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes until lightly browned.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Form into balls.
Fry until brown on all sides.
Simmer in remaining tomato sauce and 1 1/2 cans of water.
Cook 45 minutes with lid on.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Crush 1 cup strawberries.
Add water; cook for 2 minutes. Strain.
Mix cornstarch with sugar.
Stir into hot mixture and boil.
Stir constantly until thickened and clear.
Add about 5 drops of red food coloring; cool to room temperature.
Place remaining berries, stem end down, in pie shell; pour glaze over berries.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Top with whipped cream.

title: savory sloppy joes
directions: Brown and drain meat. Add barbecue sauce, green pepper and onion. Cover and cook for 15 minutes. For each sandwich, spoon meat mixture onto bottom half of bun. Cover with cheese slices. Broil until cheese begins to melt. Serve with top half of bun. Makes 8 sandwiches.

title: whiskey sour punch
directions: Mix all together and add sugar if needed.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Cut off tops of peppers.
Clean out seeds and wash thoroughly.
Cook peppers for 5 minutes in 5 cups salted water. Drain.

title: marie's best brownies
directions: Place all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Beat for 3 minutes.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Frost with chocolate frosting, if desired.

title: rolled boston roast(jewish brisket or chuck)
directions: I use rolled roast or rump roast.
Cook the day before you plan to serve.
Remove net or string from meat.
Place in pan. Put soup mix and wine over meat; cover and bake at 300° for 5 to 6 hours.
Halfway through, turn roast over.
Remove meat; skim off grease.
Slice meat thin.
Store in juice overnight.
Warm in juice to serve.

title: ambrosia freeze
directions: Beat together cream cheese and confectioners sugar; gradually beat in sour cream and orange juice concentrate.
Whip cream; fold into cream cheese mixture.
Add fruit cocktail and mandarin orange sections.
Spread in 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Freeze until firm.
Let stand at room temperature about 10 minutes before serving.
Serve on lettuce leaves; sprinkle with coconut.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: brandy slush
directions: Stir and freeze a few days before use.
Stir a few times each day.
Serve 2/3 slush with 1/3 diet 7-Up.
Garnish with orange slice and cherry.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Prepare veggies per directions on package.
In a separate bowl, mix soup, sour cream and 1/2 of the Swiss cheese.
Add pepper; mix well.
Add drained, cooked veggies.
Mix again.
Pour in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and garnish with onions.
Bake for an additional 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: gourmet sirloin tips
directions: Saute garlic in hot oil.
Add meat and brown on all sides over medium heat.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to meat.
Cover and simmer over low heat on top of range until meat is tender. Serve over rice.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: sweet and sour salad
directions: Combine vinegar, oil and sugar.
Slice onion and mushrooms. Pack into 2 (1-quart) jars and pour vinegar mixture over.
Cover tightly and let marinate overnight or at least 3 hours.
Break up lettuce and remove stems from spinach.
Combine lettuce, spinach and grated Swiss cheese in a large salad bowl.
Toss in marinated vegetables and serve immediately.
Nice side salad with lasagna or spaghetti.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and flavors.
Make paste of cocoa and food colors.
Add to first mixture, alternately.
Add flour and buttermilk.
Mix soda and vinegar in small bowl (will fizz up).
Add to batter.
Blend.
Bake in three 9-inch pans for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Let cool completely.
Cover with frosting.

title: mama's spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger.
Saute celery and onions in small amount vegetable oil.
Combine all ingredients in large stockpot.
Simmer 3 to 4 hours.

title: mounds candy bar
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients.
Press into 2 long Pyrex dishes; let chill overnight in refrigerator or place in freezer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Melt paraffin wax and chocolate chips in double boiler over low heat.
Stir frequently to blend.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grate carrots.
Pour oil over carrots and lightly toss.
Sift all dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, mixing by hand until well blended.
Add carrots to flour mixture and mix well by hand.
Spoon into three 8-inch ungreased pans.
Bake until lightly browned.
Do not overbake. Remove from pans and cool on racks.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: potato salad
directions: Cut potatoes and 3 eggs into small cubes (save 1 egg for dressing).
Mix other ingredients in a small bowl.
Mash eggs. Blend well to make dressing.
Pour dressing over potatoes and eggs; toss carefully.
Sprinkle paprika on top.

title: gooey butter brownie bars
directions: You will need a 10 x 14-inch pan greased with Pam.

title: kickin' chicken
directions: Take a chicken breast.
Put on Worcestershire sauce lightly on both sides.
Sprinkle on Lawry's seasoned salt, Italian seasoning, garlic salt and seasoned pepper.
Put chicken breasts on a large plate and put in refrigerator for 2 to 4 hours before cooking to allow seasonings to soak into the meat.
Preheat grill on medium temperature and cook 15 to 25 minutes or until meat is done. Serve with vegetables and rice.

title: cherry oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Soak the cherries in 1/2 cup hot water in a small bowl for 10 minutes, then drain well.
Cream shortening and sugars with an electric mixer unti light and fluffy.
Beat in the egg, vanilla and orange rind until all ingredients are combined well.
Sift together the flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon. Blend well.
Stir in the rolled oats.

title: hamburger cabbage casserole
directions: Fill a 1 1/2 quart casserole dish about 1/2 full of cabbage. Brown hamburger with onion (drain grease).
Put hamburger over cabbage.
Add Minute rice, soup and milk.
Grate cheese of your choice on top.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: ricotta and spinach pie (quiche)
directions: Melt butter.
Saute onions and cook until soft.
Add spinach. In a large bowl combine:
Ricotta, spinach and onions.
Add eggs and other ingredients.
Bake in round pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Eat.

title: peanut pudding torte
directions: Blend together dry roasted peanuts, flour and butter. Put in 9 x 13-inch cake pan and bake at 350°
for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: wassail
directions: Heat all ingredients except oranges; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Strain punch and pour into punch bowl.
Float oranges in bowl.
Yields about 16 servings.

title: green pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover; refrigerate 4 hours before serving.
Yields 12 servings.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Add all ingredients to a baking dish.
Mix well.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Stir several times during baking.

title: mandarin orange fluff
directions: Pour marshmallows in a large bowl. Drain mandarin oranges and tear segments in two. Add sour cream and mix. Chill.

title: old nana's sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Combine flour, salt, cream of tartar and baking soda; add to butter and sugar mixture.
Chill dough for 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in sugar and place on lightly greased cookie sheet and press flat with sugared bottom of glass.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: venison tidbits
directions: Cut bacon into strips and wrap around pieces of venison. Secure with a toothpick. Make about 2 dozen. Put bacon wrapped meat into skillet; add water, salt, pepper and sauce. Boil rapidly until water is almost gone. Reduce heat and cover. Continue cooking at low heat until meat is brown, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: crunchy hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and potato chips.
Place in greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle cheese over mixture, then potato chips.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until cheese bubbles.
Yields 4 servings.

title: grilled corn-on-the-cob
directions: Pull shucks back to end of cob.
Remove silks.
Place corn in salted water; let soak for 1 hour.
Remove from water; drain well. Spread butter over corn.
Fold shucks back in place; tie with wire. Roast on grill for about 10 minutes.
Turn and roast 10 more minutes.
Check to see if tender.

title: every day cake(scratch cake)
directions: Cook in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: no bake oatmeal haystacks
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil one minute.
Add peanut butter and vanilla. Remove from stove and mix well.
Very quickly mix the oats with the cooked mixture.
Drop on wax paper.
Cool.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Soak fruits in wine overnight.
Sift flour and spices together next morning.
Add to fruit.
Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Fold into fruit mix.
Add pecans.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: italian style tuna casserole
directions: Blend water into soup.
In a greased 1 1/2 quart casserole, stir in tuna, cheese, salt, rice and vegetable.
Combine bread crumbs and melted butter.
Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Makes 5 servings.

title: italian beef sandwiches
directions: Cook beef roast, slice thin, set aside.
Clean and slice green pepper.
In pan add water, Tabasco and Worcestershire sauce, beef bouillon cube, garlic, basil and thyme.
Salt and pepper to taste. Heat and serve on hard rolls.
(Do not boil beef; will make beef tough).
Add green peppers and simmer until green peppers soften. Cool, add beef and marinate for 4 hours.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients. Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: luscious potatoes
directions: Mix together (except 2 cups grated Cheddar cheese) and put in a casserole dish.
Top with 2 cups grated Cheddar cheese and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 10.

title: grandma naclerio's meatballs(serving size - adaptable)
directions: The above is the basic recipe and can be doubled or tripled according to need as long as the increase is in proportion to the above.
Mix ingredients together.
To be sure the mix is properly balanced, roll a meat ball and if it comes away from your hand but feels sticky and holds together, the bread crumb/egg balance is correct.
Meat balls may be fried and then put in marinara sauce or fried and marinara sauce poured over them, or cooked in the marinara sauce, or eaten as is.
Can also be made very small for hors d'oeuvres.
(See recipe for marinara sauce under 'soups, salads and sauces'.)
Serving size is adaptable.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix crumbs with melted margarine.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: dream jello
directions: Put cheese, Dream Whip and 1/2 cup of milk in blender; make it liquid.
Add Jell-O powder to 1 cup boiling water to dissolve. Cool to lukewarm.
Add crushed pineapple with juice into Jell-O and mix it.
Now add cheese mixture.
Put in freezer or if in a hurry, put in deep freeze for 1 hour.

title: honey balls
directions: Cream butter, margarine, vanilla and honey.
Add flour and salt.
Stir in nuts.
Chill dough.
Roll into small balls 1/2-inch in diameter.
Chill again.
Bake at 300° for 18 to 20 minutes. Roll in confectioners sugar while warm and again when cool.
Makes 96 cookies.

title: easy au gratin
directions: Melt together all except the hash browns.
Pour over the hash browns and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook noodles in salted water until tender; drain.
Mix in remaining ingredients and put in slow cooker.
Cover and cook on low for 3 to 4 hours.

title: white chili
directions: Soak beans in large bowl overnight.
Place chicken breasts in cold water in skillet.
Season to taste with salt and white pepper. Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 7 to 8 minutes.
Cool. Remove skin and bones.
Cut meat into 1/2-inch chunks and set aside.
Heat olive oil in large saucepan.
Add onion, garlic and chiles. Saute until onion is tender.
Add 1 teaspoon salt, 1/2 teaspoon white pepper, cumin, oregano, cayenne and chicken stock. Bring to boil.
Add drained beans.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 1 1/4 hours or longer until beans are tender.
Do not boil beans. Add chicken and cheese.
Stir.
Serve with white rice and tomato salsa if desired.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Spread graham cracker crumbs over the bottom of the pan.
Sprinkle coconut, then both packages of chips.
Drizzle with milk and top with nuts.
Bake 20-30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and peanut butter together.
Also, cream into the mixture the white sugar and brown sugar.
Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Gradually mix in flour, salt and baking soda.
Optional ingredients can go in last, if wanted.

title: gazpacho in a glass
directions: In food processor, combine tomatoes, cucumbers, celery and 1 cup vegetable juice; process until blended.
Add remaining ingredients; process until smooth.

title: burt's favorite split pea soup
directions: Soak peas in water overnight.
Cook salt pork 5 minutes.
Add carrots and onions.
Cook about 10 minutes until soft.
Add peas. Add seasonings and ham bone.
Cover and bring slowly to boil.
Add potatoes.
Reduce heat and simmer gently, about 2 hours.
Remove ham bone.
Strain.
Remove all meat from bone; dice and add to hot soup.
Add sugar and butter.
Add 1/2 cup thin cream if desired. Garnish with parsley.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheesy garlic bread sticks
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Melt oleo in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan in the oven.
Stir in garlic powder.
In medium bowl, mix Bisquick, water and cheese until soft ball of dough forms.
Gently smooth into a ball.
Knead this 5 times and roll into 10 x 6-inch rectangle; cut lengthwise in half.
Cut each half into 12 sticks about 3/4-inch wide.
Roll each stick in oleo mixture in pan.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: strawberry pie (easy)
directions: Mix
ingredients.
Cook
until
thick.
Pour into crust over 1 pint fresh strawberries or may use frozen strawberries. May use Cool Whip on top as desired.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: In medium saucepan, combine milk, salt, pepper and margarine, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Reserve 1/4 cup cheese for topping.
Stir in remaining cheese until melted. Add elbows.
Turn into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Sprinkle with reserved cheese.
Bake uncovered in 375° for 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet and sour stir-fry chicken
directions: Brown chicken cubes in wok skillet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray. Add peppers, carrots and garlic; stir 1 to 2 minutes. Mix cornstarch with broth until smooth and add to wok skillet along with the pineapple and its juice, the vinegar, sugar and ginger. Bring to a quick full boil, then lower heat. Cook only until sauce has thickened slightly, then serve chicken/vegetable mixture over rice.

title: orange delight salad(makes 4 servings)
directions: Mix dry Jell-O and cottage cheese.
Add drained fruit.
Mix well and stir in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.
Divide into 4 equal servings.
Each serving counts as 1 protein exchange, 1 fruit exchange, 58 calories (optional exchange)

title: pink panther salad
directions: Makes a large amount.
May be frozen.
Great Christmas salad.

title: easy divinity
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients for 2 minutes.
Then empty marshmallow cream into medium bowl.
Pour syrup all at once into cream.
Add vanilla and beat until thick.
May add one cup pecans if desired.
Drop by teaspoonful on wax paper.

title: swiss steak
directions: Saute onions until soft.
Mix flour, salt and pepper; pound into both sides of steak.
Brown both sides in oil in pan.
Add mustard, Worcestershire sauce, hot sauce, onion soup and water. Cover and simmer 2 1/2 hours until tender when pierced.
Remove meat to platter; skim fat from broth in pan.
Thicken broth with flour mixed to a smooth paste with a small amount of water, if desired.

title: rice krispies squares
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a full boil and cook until it spins a thread.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and Rice Krispies; mix.
Pour into a buttered or Pam sprayed pan.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Use 2 to 3 teaspoons to a cup of hot water.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini until tender.
Mash and drain well.
Squeeze excess water out.
Combine with all other ingredients except cheese and eggs; stir well.
Fold in eggs.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart greased dish.
Bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour or until top is golden brown and a knife comes out clean. Serves 4 to 6.

title: bacon, lettuce, tomato dip
directions: In a large bowl, combine bacon, tomato, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Add spinach, if desired, first squeezing out all moisture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with toasted squares.

title: black bean soup
directions: Combine soup, bouillon, water and onion in saucepan.
Stirring often, simmer until onion is soft.
Let soup cool to lukewarm and stir in sour cream.
Add sherry and also salt and pepper if needed.
Reheat.
Float a lemon slice on each serving.
Sometimes instead of a lemon slice, I put a huge spoon of salsa on top and garnish with fresh cilantro.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: rick's best beer chili
directions: Brown all meat and drain well.
Combine all ingredients in a large pot.
Cover and simmer for 2 hours or until meat is tender. Enjoy.

title: blueberry pie *
directions: Allow cheese to soften at room temperature.
Cream together cheese and sugar; fold in Cool Whip.
Spread mixture into pie shells.
Chill for at least 1 hour.
Just before serving, top with pie filling.
Makes two 9-inch pies.

title: russian salad
directions: Combine jello, water, cheese and marshmallows.
Dissolve over low heat.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into mold or Pyrex dish. Let set in refrigerator.

title: smoked sausage, onions and white potatoes
directions: In a pot,
cover the cut sausage and onions with water; boil for 30 minutes.
Add the potatoes and cook until potatoes are tender.
Serves 4 to 7.
A delicious quick winter meal.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Let cheese and oleo soften at room temperature.
Blend.
Stir in flour (chill optional).
Shape in 2 dozen 1-inch balls. Place in tiny ungreased 1 3/4-inch muffin tins.
Press dough against bottom and sides of cup.

title: chili con queso
directions: Combine all ingredients in a crock-pot on low heat.
Serve with tortilla or corn chips.

title: deep fried mozzarella
directions: Put eggs, flour and bread crumbs in separate bowls.
Dip cheese in egg, flour, egg, then bread crumbs.
Place on baking sheet with wax paper in refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Put in hot oil; fry until golden brown (375° in deep fryer).

title: egg and cheese casserole
directions: Place alternate layers of bread, cheese and sausage in greased 9 x 12-inch (2-quart) baking dish.
Beat eggs and milk; add salt and pepper.
Pour over bread layers and refrigerate overnight.

title: meat pinwheels
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
In a small bowl, mix biscuit mix and milk. Form a soft dough.
Roll out dough on a floured board into a 12-inch square.
Mix margarine, catsup, mustard and onion; spread evenly over dough.
Roll up jelly-roll fashion and cut into 8 slices.
Place on baking pan and bake 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Prepare gravy mix, serve with pinwheels.

title: batter-fried squash(or any other veggie you want to batter-fry.)
directions: Stir the dry ingredients together until well mixed.
Add egg and water; blend until smooth.
Wash squash well and slice into thin slices, about 1/4-inch thick.
Dip each slice into batter and fry in enough hot oil to cover.

title: miss kay's whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter well.
Add eggs, one at a time, and cream well.
Add flour and cream alternately to creamed mixture. Beat well.
Add vanilla and almond extracts.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
(Put in cold oven.)
Delicious for strawberry shortcake.

title: best ever sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the sugars and butter or margarine.
Combine with remaining ingredients and mix well.
Roll into balls about the size of a small walnut.
Place 2 inches apart on a greased cookie sheet.
Press with the bottom of a glass dipped in sugar. Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Watch carefully.
Makes about 100 cookies.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Combine and mix the flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder and baking soda. Add milk, oleo and vanilla. Beat on low speed until well mixed, then on medium for 2 minutes. Add egg; beat 2 minutes more. Bake in greased 9 x 1 1/2-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Simmer celery, onion, mushrooms and pimentos in the oleo about 10 minutes.
Add soup and chicken; cook 5 minutes.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Add milk to thin to desired consistency.
Add cooked spaghetti and mix well.
Turn into a 9 x 13-inch casserole and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican meat dish
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Brown meat and onions.
Add all ingredients except cheese and chips and let simmer in a casserole dish.
Layer chips in bottom.
Pour mixture in.
Cook 25 minutes. Take out, put grated cheese on top and put back in oven long enough to melt cheese.

title: choconut caramel bars
directions: Melt over hot (not boiling) water the chocolate chips and vegetable shortening.
Stir until chips melt and mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat.
Pour 1/2 of melted chocolate into an 8-inch foil-lined square pan; spread evenly.
Refrigerate until firm (about 15 minutes).
Return remaining chocolate mix to low heat.
Combine over boiling water the caramels, butter and water. Stir until caramels melt and mixture is smooth.
Stir in nuts until well blended.
Pour into the chocolate lined pan.
Spread evenly.
Refrigerate until tacky, about 15 minutes.
Top with remaining melted chocolate; spread evenly to cover caramel filling.
Return to refrigerator and chill until firm (about 1 hour).
Cut into 1 x 2-inch rectangles.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen candies.

title: mud hen bars
directions: Cream shortening and white sugar.
Beat in whole egg and 2 egg yolks.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Combine with creamed mixture.
Spread batter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts, marshmallows and chocolate chips over batter.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in brown sugar.
Spread on top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Cut into bars.

title: wild rice salad
directions: Cook rice according to package directions, omitting salt or substituting seasoned salt.
Drain well.
Cool to room temperature.
Spoon into large bowl.
Add chicken, grapes, water chestnuts and mayonnaise.
Toss with fork.
Cover and chill.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Pour cider or juice in a large pan. Add sugar and heat. Do not boil. Wrap next 3 ingredients in a mesh or cloth bag. Drop bag into the hot cider. Add the cinnamon stick. Cook for about 20 minutes. Makes 1 gallon and makes your kitchen smell good!!

title: hamburger chop suey
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and celery.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Bake in oven for 1 hour at 375°.

title: lite chocolate fondue
directions: Combine cornstarch, cocoa and sugar.
Add water and vanilla. Stir until smooth.
Cook over medium heat until mixture boils, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Serve as a dip with fresh fruit.
Makes 1 cup.

title: frozen salad
directions: Combine all ingredients for individual servings.
Line muffin tins; freeze.
Will keep frozen at least 3 months, wrapped individually and placed in freezer bags.
Can also freeze in a block.
Before cutting, let set at room temperature about 5 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate macaroon bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine graham crackers, sugar, cocoa and butter; press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
In medium bowl combine remaining ingredients; mix well. Spoon evenly over prepared crust.
Bake 30 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool and cut into bars.
Store covered in refrigerator. Makes 24 to 36 bars.

title: tuna vegetable chowder
directions: Melt margarine in top half of a double boiler over boiling water.
Add flour and stir until a paste is formed.
Stir in water gradually.
Add seasoning mix.
Cook and stir until thickened. Add zucchini and green onion.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients except parsley.
Heat until hot.
Garnish with chopped parsley.
Makes 2 servings.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Line entire cupcake pan with biscuits.
Add barbecue to the top of biscuit.
Sprinkle generous amount of Cheddar cheese.
Bake according to package.

title: mock turkey
directions: Beat eggs; add the remaining ingredients.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Place in an 8-inch square pan (sprayed with Pam).
This is equally very tasty cold for sandwiches.

title: cold ham - pasta salad
directions: Combine salad dressing, cheese and milk; mix well.
Add all remaining ingredients, except lettuce.
Mix lightly.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Serve on lettuce covered platter.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Add celery and cook 10 minutes.
Add all remaining ingredients, except green peppers.
Simmer, covered, 30 minutes. Add peppers, simmer 15 minutes more.
Flavor improves with reheating.

title: rice and tofu loaf
directions: Crumble or mash tofu into a bowl.
Heat oil in skillet and saute onion, garlic and leek, adding Herbamare and dried herbs. Add carrot and continue to saute for a few minutes until veggies are soft.
Add veggies and other ingredients to tofu and mix well. Transfer to oiled loaf pan or casserole dish; cover with foil and put in preheated 375° oven.
After 30 minutes, remove foil and continue to cook for another 15 minutes until golden and slightly crisp on top.
Allow to cook for approximately 20 minutes before removing from pan and slicing.
Delicious served with Sesame Miso sauce.

title: tasty french bread
directions: Slice French bread and place on cookie sheet.
Spread with mayonnaise or salad dressing.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and parsley flakes.
Place in hot oven and bake until bread begins to brown.
(Very good with spaghetti dishes.)

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Place frozen broccoli in Pyrex dish and microwave for approximately 5 minutes.
Add to cooked rice.
Stir in mushroom soup, chopped onion and pimientos.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Mix milk, sugar and flour well.
Melt butter in 2-quart baking dish.
Pour in flour mixture.
Pour in pie filling.
Do not stir. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until flour mixture rises to top.

title: chicken and rice salad
directions: Combine rice, French dressing, onion, salt and pepper.	Let this stand about 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and toss lightly.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve with pepper rings and boiled eggs if you wish.
Put on lettuce.	Sprinkle with paprika.	Adjust amounts according to taste.

title: chicken parmesan pizza(makes 4 to 6 servings)
directions: Dredge chicken in flour.
Pour oil into large skillet 1-inch deep.
Heat oil over medium-high heat until hot.
Add chicken; fry until chicken is tender and golden brown.
Remove to a paper towel with slotted spoon to absorb excess oil.
Spread 1 cup tomato sauce over Boboli Italian bread shell, leaving 1-inch border. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Top with chicken, remaining 1 cup tomato sauce and olives.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese and oregano.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet in lower 1/3 of oven at 450° for about 8 to 10 minutes or until puffed and lightly browned.

title: microwave fettuccini alfredo
directions: Place cooked fettuccini in 2-quart casserole dish.
Stir in light cream, sour cream, margarine, green onion and garlic powder. Heat on full power 5 to 7 minutes, or until heated through.
Stir in Parmesan cheese.
Serve immediately.

title: pineapple coconut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Let eggs and butter get to room temperature.
Cream Crisco, butter and sugar together.
Add eggs one at a time.
Alternately add flour, milk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Make 4 (9-inch) layers and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: christmas wassail
directions: Simmer until hot and spicy.
(Can use apple juice concentrate to sweeten.)

title: toffee candy
directions: Melt butter, stir in
sugar
and
add
water and syrup. Simmer until it reaches a temperature of 290°.
Pour in finely chopped pecans.
Spread in	a
thin buttered pan.
Melt chocolate
chips in double
boiler.	Spread	on
after
toffee
has cooled.	When chocolate is cooled, break into pieces and store in an airtight container.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed.
Mix all ingredients together and put into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes until thoroughly heated.

title: mom's zucchini cake
directions: Cream margarine, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour milk.
Beat with a mixer.
Add dry ingredients.
Beat well.
Stir in zucchini.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts and chocolate chips evenly over batter.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: zucchini and summer squash pickles
directions: In earthenware crock or stainless steel, glass or enamel container, arrange a layer each of squash, onions and peppers; salt top layer liberally.
Continue layering with remaining vegetables and salt.
Cover; set aside one hour.
Drain off liquid and rinse well.
In large pot over medium-high heat, bring vinegar, sugar, mustard seed and celery seed to boil.
Add vegetables; return to boil.
After 10 seconds, remove from heat.
Ladle into hot sterilized jars to 1/4-inch from top.
Seal.
Process 5 minutes in a boiling water bath.
Makes 4 pints.

title: feather dumplings
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add egg, margarine and enough milk to make moist, stiff batter.
Drop by teaspoon or roll out and cut into strips and drop into boiling broth.
Cover and cook for 18 minutes.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Mix all together and cold pack 1/2 hour.
Makes 3 or 4 pies.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; add sugar.
Grind cranberries and apples; add to gelatin with the remaining ingredients. Refrigerate overnight.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onions.
Brown steak which has been cut in thin strips. Combine onions, steak, soup, mushrooms, catsup and Worcestershire sauce.
Heat together. Add sour cream just before serving. Serve over cooked noodles.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Fry meat; drain off grease.
Then add beans and rice.
Cook until hot. Grate cheese, then layer the casserole with the cheese. Serve with chips.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli in water for 4 minutes; drain.
Put into casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese over this.
Combine soup and milk and pour over broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, uncovered. Top with fried onions last 10 minutes.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Make crust by combining first 3 ingredients.
Combine next 4 ingredients and cook on low heat until thickened.
Add butter and vanilla after cooked.
Pour into pie shell.
Make a meringue of egg whites.
Cover pie and brown at 350° for 20 minutes or until browned.

title: crab au gratin
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed and drain.
Combine with soup, mayonnaise, egg and onion.
Add stuffing mix and mix well.
Grease casserole with butter.
Put mixture into casserole dish and dot with the remaining butter.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: walnut turtles
directions: Place caramels in top of double boiler with butter.
Set over boiling water.
Heat until completely melted, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Stir well.
Add nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful.
Melt Crisco and chocolate over hot, not boiling water.
Spread over candies and allow to set.
Makes 28 to 30 pieces.

title: artichoke and crab spread
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms.
Add wine and simmer 1 minute. Combine mayonnaise, cheese and all other ingredients except paprika.
Put mixture in a quiche dish or large pie plate, sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in 350° oven until bubbly.
About 25 minutes. Serve with rye rounds or any other crackers.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Barely cover with water.
Cook until mushy, about one hour, until almost dry.
Add:

title: royal pudding brownie cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Pour into greased pan, brownie size.
Dot with pieces of margarine.
Pour water over the batter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped topping (optional).

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Place ribs, bone down in roaster pan; top with sliced onions. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over ribs; cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours; uncover and bake 20 to 30 minutes longer. Great with rice or noodles.

title: christmas brunch
directions: You will need an ungreased 2 x 9 x 13 pan.

title: red satin punch
directions: Combine ingredients in large punch bowl. Serve chilled. Yields 50 servings.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Sprinkle sugar on top.

title: banana muffins
directions: Cream the sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and pureed bananas. Cream all of them well. Pour in flour and baking powder. Add all the rest of the ingredients.
Grease muffin tin and bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: oven stew
directions: Combine all ingredients together in large casserole dish. Cook in oven for 4 hours at 250°.
Additional seasonings may be added to taste.

title: chicken noodle bake
directions: Brown onion in butter. Stir in soup, milk and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Heat until cheese melts. Blend with noodles.
Pour into a buttered 3-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle on crumbs or onions and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: white bread(4 loaves)
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
In large 4-quart bowl, mix sugar, shortening, salt and milk until shortening is melted.
Add cold water; cool to lukewarm.
Stir in yeast.
Gradually add flour to form a stiff dough.
Knead on floured surface until smooth and satiny, 5 to 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease all sides.
Cover with foil or damp cloth.
Let rise for 2 hours. Punch down and fold in edges, let raise again 30 minutes.
Place on floured surface and divide into 4 portions.
Put in greased loaf pans, let raise 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: meal-in-one
directions: Saute meat in large, heavy skillet or saucepan on low heat. Stir and separate particles until color changes.
Do not brown. Pour off excess fat.
Add salt, pepper, chili mix and catsup. Continue cooking on low heat about 20 minutes.
Add mushrooms, chestnuts, tomatoes and corn.
Continue cooking about 10 more minutes.
Pour into large casserole dish.

title: foolproof sloppy joes
directions: Brown and drain ground beef; leave in skillet.
Add soup, ketchup, and mustard.
Mix well and simmer until well heated. Serve.
Can also make larger quantities and keep warm in a crock-pot.

title: clams
directions: Pour milk into top of double boiler.
Sprinkle flour and seasoning over surface.
Beat with rotary beater until blended. Cook over hot water, stirring constantly, until mixture has thickened.

title: bacon and cheese oven pancake
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Combine egg, milk and drippings.
Add all at once to dry mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in crumbled bacon.

title: hot and sour soup(makes 8 to 12 servings)
directions: Freeze pork for about 30 minutes.
Using sharp knife, shred into pieces about 1/4-inch wide.
Put dried mushrooms in bowl and pour boiling water over to cover.
Let stand for 15 minutes until soft.
Drain and rinse mushrooms to remove sand.
Remove hard spots and tough stems.
Cut into shreds the same size as pork. Place shredded pork into bowl and add sherry and half the soy sauce, cornstarch and sesame oil.
Stir well.

title: potato dumplings
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets until tender.
Remove skins and put through ricer into bowl.
Add salt, eggs, flour, bread crumbs or farina, nutmeg and chopped onion.
Mix thoroughly.
Form mixture into dry balls about the size of a plum.
If the mixture is too moist, add more bread crumbs or farina.
Drop balls into salted boiling water (about 4 or 5 at a time).
When balls come to the surface, allow to boil 3 minutes.
Remove from liquid and test to see if inside is dry.
They are done if inside is dry.
They may be reheated in a double boiler, if necessary.
When forming balls, I put a crouton in middle of ball and make sure my hands are floured at all times.
Good Luck!
Makes 26 balls.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Mix together potatoes, soup, onions, butter and sour cream.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Remove from oven, sprinkle grated cheese on top and return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: margaret's ham
directions: Place ham in shallow foil lined pan.
Pour apple juice over the ham.
Wrap foil tightly around ham.
Bake at 225° overnight. Makes good sandwiches.

title: easy sweet potato pie
directions: Put ingredients into blender.
Beat until smooth.
Pout into two (2) unbaked pie shells.
Bake 10 minute at 425°.
Reduce to 325° and bake 40 minutes or until done.

title: nellie's potatoes
directions: Place several large potatoes, sliced thin, in greased casserole dish.
Dot with butter; pour can of soup over potatoes and add milk to thin soup and mix.
Bake at 350° until slices are tender.

title: swedish meat balls and sauce
directions: For meat balls, mix beef, pork, bread crumbs, half and half, onion, salt, allspice, Worcestershire sauce, pepper and egg. Shape into 30 (1-inch) balls.
Cook in 10-inch skillet over medium heat about 20 minutes, turning often until brown. Drain meat balls. Stir in soup, half and half and nutmeg.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes. Stir in sour cream; heat through. Sprinkle with parsley.

title: melt aways
directions: Melt butter in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter in pan.
Add layers of chocolate morsels, butterscotch morsels, nuts and coconut.
Pour condensed milk over top and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes then cut into bars.

title: mushroom, onion and pepper saute
directions: Heat oil in large skillet and saute until vegetables are tender.
Salt and pepper.
Tasty side dish for steaks or hamburgers.

title: almond bark cookies
directions: Melt almond bark in double boiler or microwave.
Mix the rest of ingredients in a large bowl and stir in melted bark.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper or put in large pan and cut in squares.

title: cranberry glazed pork
directions: Combine cornstarch, cinnamon, salt and orange peel in a small saucepan. Stir in orange juice, sherry and cranberry sauce.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened. Set aside.

title: mom's chocolate icing
directions: Boil sugar, milk, cocoa and Karo until mixture is to the soft boil stage.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Beat mixture until thick.
Ice cake.

title: pat's all state fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk in a large saucepan.
Boil 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add chocolate chips; stir in.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Stir until thick.
Add nuts, if desired.
Pour into greased pan.
Cool 6 hours.
Makes 5 pounds of fudge.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape in roll or put in tube pan. Slice as wanted.

title: easy beignets(french market donuts)
directions: Open can of biscuits. Roll out each biscuit until very thin. Then cut into fourths.
Fry in hot oil until nice and brown.
Take out and shake in container with confectioners sugar while hot. Take out and serve while still hot.
Great with milk coffee.

title: italian cream cheese cake(club member: renee evans)
directions: Beat egg whites; set aside.
Cream butter, egg yolks, sugar and Crisco together.
Sift flour and soda.
Add to sugar mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Beat well.
Add vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake 1 hour in tube pan or at 350° for 25 minutes in layer pan (makes 3 layers).

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes and combine in a large bowl with 1/2 cup melted butter.
Add salt, pepper, onions, soup, sour cream and cheese. Blend thoroughly.
Pour into large greased 9 x 13-inch casserole; top with buttered corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Mix the night before to blend flavor.
This is great for celery, carrot sticks or green pepper strips.
Any raw vegetables and exceptionally good on baked potatoes.

title: baked chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix together the stuffing mix, chicken broth and butter.
Put into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix chicken, mayonnaise and chopped onion; spread over the stuffing mixture.
Beat eggs and 1 1/2 cups milk; pour evenly over casserole.

title: instant fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail.
Toss fruit with grated cheese.
Serve on lettuce leaves with or without dressing.
Yields 4 servings.

title: cherry cream cheese dessert
directions: In bowl, combine cracker crumbs, sugar and butter. Divide among 8 dessert dishes, about 4 rounded teaspoonfuls in each. In a small mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth. Gradually add milk until blended. Beat in lemon juice and vanilla. Spoon 1/4 cup into each dish. Top with pie filling, about 1/4 cup each. May use apple or strawberry pie filling. Top with whipped cream if desired. Makes 8 servings.

title: charlie's cuckoo's nest
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place all slices of French bread on bottom of pan.
In large bowl, beat together milk and eggs.
Pour all egg mixture over bread slices.
Pour butter on top of bread. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.
Top with bacon.

title: deviled english peas
directions: Layer peas, egg slices, pimento and cheese in casserole dish. Spread
half
of the soup over the top.
Repeat layers. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cover with onion rings and heat until hot.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In a large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and water. Add pudding mix.
Beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.

title: butter-pecan bread
directions: Beat egg and add sugar, butter and buttermilk.
Add to this mixture the sifted dry ingredients and the pecans.
Bake 1 big or 3 small (baked in medium size fruit cocktail cans).
Grease containers and dust with flour.
Fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes for small loaves, longer for large.

title: daddy's pound cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, cream of tartar and salt. Sift at least 2 to 3 times.
Cream sugar, butter, margarine and Crisco.
Add eggs to sugar mixture 2-1-2.
Mix well after each addition.
Put vanilla in milk.
Alternately add flour mixture and milk to sugar/shortening mixture.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Cook at 325° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
(Can use for layer cake, 30 to 35 minutes.)

title: cherry fruit squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly; add vanilla.
Stir in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in flour; add nuts and mix well.
Spread 3/4 of thick batter into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with cherry pie filling. Drop remaining batter by spoonfuls on filling and spread with spatula.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool and cut for finger pastries.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: dilly bread
directions: Mix yeast and water.
Set aside to bubble.
Heat cottage cheese and butter until warm.
Combine with remainder of ingredients except flour.
Beat well.
Add yeast and mix.
Add flour gradually. Let stand 1 hour.
Punch down.
Place in well-greased loaf pan. Let rise another hour.
Bake about 45 minutes.

title: asparagus roll-ups
directions: Cut crusts from bread and roll thin with rolling pin.
Spread one side with mixture of 2/3 Blue cheese and 1/3 mayonnaise. Place 1 stalk asparagus on each piece of bread.
Roll up.
Brush with melted butter.
Bake at 425° until brown.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: In large saucepan on stove, mix all ingredients, except meatballs, together.
When thoroughly blended, stir in your favorite meatballs and let them simmer in the sauce for hours. (They can be made the day before you need them.)

title: canned potatoes for scallops
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Pack in clean canning pint or quart jars.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt to each quart of potatoes.
Pour boiling water to fill each jar; seal.
Place in hot water bath for 20 minutes.

title: jalapeno cheese corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into sprayed 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: portobello and brie cups
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Spray 24 miniature muffin cups with nonstick cooking spray. Clean mushrooms; finely chop.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cook bacon, let it cool, crumble into tiny pieces and set aside.
Bring a pot of 4 cups of water to boil, empty package of broccoli slaw into boiling water and let boil for only 5 minutes, drain and rinse with cool water.
Put slaw in serving boil, mix in bacon, sunflower seeds, and raisins.
In a small bowl, mix together the mayonnaise, vinegar, and sugar until well blended. Stir dressing into broccoli mix and serve or refrigerate until ready.

title: apple squares
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon onto wax paper. Melt butter in medium-size saucepan over moderate heat.
Remove from heat.
Beat in sugars, egg and vanilla with a wooden spoon until smooth

title: sweet-sour pork
directions: Trim fat from pork.
Brown in oil in a large skillet.
Remove and set aside.
Add to skillet the bell pepper, celery and onion. Saute lightly and drain.
Add to skillet rest of ingredients. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Return pork chops to skillet.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes over low heat.

title: rich rice pudding
directions: In 4-quart saucepan over medium heat, heat milk, rice and salt to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add raisins and sugar; simmer 20 minutes longer or until rice is very tender.
Pour rice mixture into large bowl and refrigerate until well chilled.

title: egg yolk noodles
directions: Sift dry ingredients together, work in shortening.
Make a well in center and add egg yolks and milk (eggs and milk blended together).
Blend ingredients with fork, turn out on well floured board and knead until smooth, adding more flour if necessary.
Roll out as thin as possible, let stand 20 minutes.
Cut into narrow strips, shaking them together with a dusting of flour.

title: seven-minute frosting
directions: Put in double boiler; have water boiling and beat for 7 minutes or until thick enough to spread on cake.

title: eggs a la caracas
directions: Cut dried beef fine with scissors.
Add tomatoes, cheese, onion juice, cinnamon and cayenne.
Melt in an omelet pan butter; add the mixture and heat 5 minutes.
Add 3 eggs, well beaten. Stir and cook over direct heat until creamy.

title: scalloped corn and rice
directions: Mix rice, corn, green pepper and pimiento together.
Season, as desired, with salt and pepper.
Blend in eggs; place in a greased 2-quart casserole in alternate layers with cheese, allowing for cheese to be on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 4 to 6.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg and vanilla and beat well. Add milk with the dry ingredients and blend all together. Fold in the diced rhubarb. Pour into greased 13 x 9 pan.

title: fruit-nut pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, alternately with small amounts of flour until all flour and eggs have been used.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into 2 loaf pans that have been lightly greased and floured.
Stuff cherries down into batter one at a time until you have as many cherries in as you might want.
The cherry juice is not used.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: oven pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place margarine in "pancake pan" and heat in oven for about 2 minutes or until margarine melts.
Spread melted margarine evenly over bottom of pan.
Set aside.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Mix the meat, garlic, onions and seasonings together.
Clean the bell peppers and stuff with meat mixture.

title: italian wedding soup
directions: Cook noodles in water according to directions.
In another pan, bring broth to a boil.
In mixing bowl, mix next 6 ingredients with your hands.
Form into grape size balls and drop into stock.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Add spinach and noodles.
Cook until spinach is heated.
Serve immediately with Parmesan cheese as garnish.
Great with crusty bread!

title: corn cob jelly
directions: Boil broken cobs in the water for 30 minutes.
Remove from heat and strain the liquid.
If not 3 cups, add enough water to make 3 cups.
Add pectin and bring to a rolling boil.
Add sugar; cook 2 to 3 minutes or until jelly stage.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Wash and hull strawberries.
Remove half (the best looking ones) and mash the rest.
Add sugar and cornstarch.
Mix well and cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly, until thickened and clear. Stir in lemon juice.
Cool.
Add the remaining strawberries, saving 6 for garnish.
Pour into the pie shell and chill.
Before serving, top with the whipped cream and garnish with the remaining 6 strawberries.

title: quick chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in bottom of baking dish.
Bring to a boil cream of chicken soup and broth.
Stir until smooth.
Add chopped eggs and peas.
Pour over chicken.
Melt oleo, add flour and milk, pour over top.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: rhubarb custard cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chopped rhubarb over cake batter.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Pour the cream over everything.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Enjoy warm.
(Can also use peaches or blueberries instead of the rhubarb.)

title: dill pickles
directions: Choose crisp, fresh picked cucumbers.
Wash through 2 or 3 cold waters, rubbing with hands, never a brush.
Put vinegar, salt and water into large kettle ready for heating.
Wash dill and grape leaves.
Have ready 8 or 9 clean quart jars.
Place dill in each jar.
Pack sliced cucumbers, leaving room to put dill and grape leaf and 2 1/8-inch slice red pepper and 1/8 teaspoon alum in each jar.
Heat vinegar, salt and water to boiling and pour over pickles to fill jars.
Seal.
Store in cool, dark place.
Ready to use in 6 to 8 weeks.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix.
Pour half of it in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Melt Kraft caramels with butter and evaporated milk.
Pour over cake.
Sprinkle with pecans and chocolate bits over caramel.
Top with remainder of cake mix. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy herbed loaf
directions: Slice the loaf into 1-inch thick slices, cutting to but not through bottom.
Combine butter, green onions, parsley, thyme, marjoram and garlic salt in a small bowl; mix well.
Spread on bread slices.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Yields 16 servings.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine and form into golf ball sized balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes until golden brown. Serve with dipping sauces.

title: shrimp au gratin
directions: Alternate layers of cleaned, cooked shrimp, white sauce and 1/2 cup cheese in greased baking dish. Sprinkle with parsley and remaining cheese, then buttered crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until crumbs are brown.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Pour over carrots and toss lightly.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: party sausages
directions: Cut each wiener into 3 pieces.
Cut each piece of bacon in half.
Wrap around the little wiener and stick with toothpick. Lay in Pyrex dish and sprinkle brown sugar on top of wieners. Cook for 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 30.

title: creamy beef dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Makes 3 cups.
Serve as a dip with vegetables.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: cherry pecan pound cake
directions: In a large bowl, beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, vanilla, almond, salt and nutmeg.
Beat until thoroughly blended.
Stir in flour, 1/2 cup at a time, mixing just until blended.
Stir in cherries and pecans.
Spread batter evenly in greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 60 to 70 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cool in pan on wire rack for 10 minutes. Loosen edges.
Remove from pan.
Cool completely on wire rack.

title: hot brown
directions: Cook in double boiler or heavy pan.
Toast 1 piece of bread. Add 1 slice of turkey breast.
Cover with cheese sauce.
Add slices of tomatoes and 2 pieces of crisp bacon per serving.
Place on cookie sheet and heat thoroughly under broiler just before serving.

title: black forest sundaes
directions: Place brownies on individual serving plates.
Top each brownie with a scoop of ice cream and some cherry pie filling.
Top with whipped cream.
Serve immediately.

title: spice tea
directions: Add 2 teaspoons per cup of hot water.
Contains 4 calories per cup.

title: sausage with long grain rice casserole
directions: Cook rice until tender.
Cook sausage and drain.
Stir in mushroom soup.
Layer rice and sausage mixture into a buttered dish.
Layer sliced onion on top of each layer.
Cover and cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peach salad
directions: Mix jello and pineapple in saucepan; heat, but don't boil. Let cool for 20 minutes. Stir in buttermilk, Mandarin oranges, Cool Whip and 1 cup nuts. Sprinkle top with remaining crushed nuts. Place in refrigerator to congeal overnight. Serves 18.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well and add next 2.
This mixture will be soft and tacky.
Can add more flour if needed.
Bake plain crust at 375° until done.

title: barbecued ham
directions: Combine
pineapple
juice,
brown
sugar,
lemon juice, onion salt
and
soy sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered,	for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Trim excess fat from ham slices.
Grill over medium heat for 20 to 30 minutes. Turn slices and baste with sauce.
Grill 1 minute on
each	side. Garnish
ham
with pineapple slices and serve with remaining sauce.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and cream together, chop eggs and mix. Smooth out top in large bowl.
Add paprika to top for decoration.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Combine ingredients in order given.
