Cover bowl lightly and refrigerate overnight for flavors to blend.

title: guess what?(graham cracker brittle)
directions: Use jelly roll pan.
Line it with graham crackers; sprinkle chopped pecans over crackers.
Cook sugar and butter for 2 minutes. Pour over crackers and pecans.
Then bake at 350° about 10 to 12 minutes.
Let cool, then break.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Add oats to boiling water; set 20 minutes.
Add brown sugar, white sugar and butter; cream together.
Add eggs, soda, cinnamon, salt and flour.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream shortening and sugar lightly.
Add egg. Then add dry ingredients just until blended.
Do not overmix.
Add blueberries or fruit at last.
Makes 12 medium muffins.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in 400° oven.
Lightly glaze for special touch.

title: everyday lasagne
directions: Brown meat with onion, garlic and spices.
Drain and add tomato sauce.
Simmer.
Boil noodles and drain.
Add 2 tablespoons butter, sour cream and cottage cheese.
Mix well. Layer in 13 x 9-inch greased casserole, ending with meat sauce.
Top with cheese.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shopper's chicken
directions: Rinse and pat dry chicken breasts.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Mix first 5 ingredients and spoon mixture onto chicken. Sprinkle with bread crumbs to cover.
Melt butter and drizzle over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: key lime sherbet
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into bread pan or other metal container and place in freezer.
When slushy, beat until frothy and freeze again.
Allow to sit out a few minutes before serving. Easy, elegant and melt in your mouth scrumptious.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Spray baking dish with Pam, put peaches in dish.
Mix flour, sugar and egg until crumbly, pour over peaches.
Melt margarine and pour over mixture.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until brown on top.

title: orange salad
directions: Heat pineapple and jello.
Add cold water.
Chill until slightly set.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and chill.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil sweet potatoes in jackets until tender; drain.
Remove skin and mash with butter.
Combine sugar, vanilla, cinnamon, nutmeg and eggs.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: devonshire cream dip
directions: Mix thoroughly until sugar is dissolved. Spoon over fruit in a bowl or use as fondue fruit type dip.

title: party chicken
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with the dried beef.
Cut chicken breasts in half.
Flatten each piece and then roll it.
Wrap bacon strips around chicken rolls, place rolls on top of beef. Mix soup and sour cream, pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 250° for 3 hours, increase to 350° for last 15 minutes to crisp bacon.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Use mixer to mix pudding and 3 cups milk. Add Cool Whip to pudding; set aside.
Mix margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add to pudding and mix well. Crumble cookies to fine crumbs.
Put thin layer of cookie crumbs, then a layer of pudding. Alternate layers, leaving cookie crumbs on top.
Let set overnight in new flowerpot or sandpail. Decorate with artificial flowers or gummy worms.

title: fruit frappe
directions: Pour boiling water into blender container.
Add Jell-O and blend at low speed until completely dissolved.
Add ice cubes; stir until partially melted and blend 2 minutes or until mixture is slightly thickened.
Add sherbet and blend.
Serve at once as beverage or pour into individual dishes and chill for 30 minutes or more.
Makes 2 1/2 cups or 5 servings.

title: tex-mex cornbread salad
directions: Crumble half of prepared cornbread into bottom of large serving bowl.
Top with half of beans.
In another bowl, combine tomatoes, onions, green pepper and jalapeno pepper; blend well. Spread half of vegetable mixture over beans.
Sprinkle with half the bacon and half of the cheese.
Stir together sour cream and salsa in small bowl; spread half of dressing over cheese.
Repeat layering procedure with remaining cornbread, beans, vegetables, bacon, cheese and dressing.
Garnish with sour cream and jalapeno pepper slices, if desired.
Cover tightly and chill two to three hours before serving.
Makes six to eight servings.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa well.
Add eggs, margarine, milk and vanilla flavoring.
Pour into an uncooked pie shell.
Bake 25 or 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix together and beat 10 minutes at medium speed.
Bake in greased pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: laura's chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken.
Once cooled slightly, shred and put in a large mixing bowl.
Mix in Ro-Tel.
Put chicken mixture and Cheddar cheese in a flour tortilla, roll and place seam-side down in a baking dish.
Repeat until dish is full.
Pour soup over the tortillas, covering completely.
Top with Monterey Jack cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: tangy brussels sprouts
directions: Place water in a medium saucepan; bring to a boil.
Add bouillon cube, stirring until dissolved.
Add Brussels sprouts; return to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 5 to 6 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Add onion and vinegar; stir gently.
Cover and chill 3 to 4 hours, stirring occasionally.
Yields 4 servings.

title: chicken a la roma
directions: Top each cutlet with 1 slice of Mozzarella cheese and 1 slice of ham.
Roll up cutlets and bread them in flour and salt, then egg, then bread crumbs.
Brown in oil and set aside.
In oblong dish or pan, place sauce on the bottom.
Place cutlets on top of sauce.
Cover with sauce and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with pasta.

title: fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with the marshmallow cream until you get a desired consistency.
(Used as fruit dip at Matherne's Grocery and Deli.)

title: fruit cake
directions: You can add rum, bourbon or brandy, if you wish, 1/4 to 1 cup depending on taste.

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: Mix peanut butter, milk and vanilla until well blended. Gradually add sugar.
Mix until smooth and of desired spreading consistency.
Yields frosting for 2 (9-inch) round layers.

title: t.v. tidbits
directions: Mix cereals, peanuts and pecans.
Heat Wesson oil.
Add remaining ingredients, except cereals, peanuts and pecans.
Pour mixture over cereal mixture; stir well.
Bake for 2 hours at 200°, stirring every 30 minutes.

title: raisin cake
directions: Cook raisins about 5 minutes (in 1 cup water).
Add soda and lard.
Cool.
Add nutmeg, cloves, cinnamon, sugar and enough flour for batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: apostle island pasta
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil until golden and remove.
Add vegetables to oil and saute.
Add tomatoes; smoosh and stir.
Add cooked pasta and saute until pasta picks up color/flavor.
Toss all with fresh grated Parmesan cheese.

title: "black" halloween punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar and water in large kettle.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
You may serve in kettle as "Witch's Brew."

title: apple cake
directions: Sift together the flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add to the other mixture, then add apples.
Mix by hand.
Bake for 60 minutes at 325°.

title: pizza meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except pizza sauce, Mozzarella, pepper and mushrooms.
Place in baking dish and bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.
Pour any excess fat off.
Top with pizza sauce, cheese, pepper and mushrooms.
Bake 10 minutes more.

title: banana split cake
directions: Crust:
Mix graham cracker crumbs and melted margarine.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch dish and brown.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Top with 1/2 cup slivered almonds.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: party bake pork chops
directions: Season chops well on both sides with salt and pepper.
Brown on both sides in lightly greased hot skillet.
Place each browned chop in a baking dish.
Top each chop with a slice of onion, 1 heaping tablespoon of rice and cover with whole tomatoes.
Add any remaining tomatoes and juice to pan. Cover tightly with lid or foil; simmer over low heat or bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: cheese potato crisps
directions: Wash and peel potatoes.
Roll in melted margarine and dip in beaten egg, then roll in cracker crumbs.
Arrange in well-greased baking dish.
Add salt and pepper to taste and dot with margarine. Cover with foil and bake at 450° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add butter and liquid.
If deep fried, use 2 cups of flour and 3 teaspoons of baking powder.
Drop by spoon in hot fat (375°).

title: weinerschnitzel
directions: Cut meat into serving pieces; pound until very thin.
Mix flour, salt and pepper;
dredge meat in flour.
Stir egg and milk together.
Dip meat in egg mixture, then in bread crumbs.
Brown on both sides; put a slice of lemon on each piece of meat and cover, cooking slowly for 15 minutes.

title: vidalia onion salad
directions: Combine torn lettuce, sliced eggs and sliced onions in large salad bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients well.
Pour over salad. Mix slightly.

title: refried beans casserole
directions: Rinse soaked pinto beans.
Put beans in large pot and cover with water.
Cook for 3 hours.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Stir and simmer until thick.
Mash down.
Layer in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Layer guacamole, sour cream, cheese and tomatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with chips as your spoon.
Eat with a side of salad.
Makes a great summer meal.

title: trees and seeds
directions: Mix Miracle Whip with sugar and lemon juice.
Combine with broccoli, onion, raisins and seeds.
Ready to serve.

title: spiral medley pasta salad
directions: Combine the cooked, drained pasta with all ingredients and allow flavors to "marry" for several hours.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain and mix peas, green beans and corn.
Add celery and onion.
Mix the following in a pan and bring to boil: salad oil, white vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
After bringing to a boil, remove from heat and let cool 5 minutes.
Pour over vegetables and refrigerate overnight.
Drain before serving.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until soft when pierced.
Remove skins and mash in an ovenproof dish with salt and butter until smooth.
Add applesauce, mix thoroughly.
Sprinkle top with mini marshmallows and place under broiler until marshmallows are lightly browned.

title: vanilla-nut icebox cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and set aside. In a large bowl, beat butter until light.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Continue beating until very light and fluffy.
At low speed, beat in 1/2 flour mixture; mix in rest with hands to form a stiff dough.
Add chopped nuts, mixing to combine well. Turn out dough onto lightly floured surface.
Divide in half.
With hands, shape each half onto a roll 7 inches long. Wrap each in plastic wrap or foil; refrigerate until firm, about 8 hours, or overnight, before slicing and baking.
(Rolls of cookie dough may be stored in refrigerator as long as 10 days.
Slice and freshly bake as many as desired.)

title: cheesy zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini into 1/4-inch slices.
Lightly grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Combine flour with 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/2 teaspoon oregano and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Toss zucchini in seasoned flour to coat well.
Slowly heat oil in large heavy skillet.
Saute zucchini until golden brown, about 4 minutes per side.
Drain.
Cover dish with zucchini; top with tomatoes. Combine sour cream, rest of salt, oregano and pepper and spread over tomatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: pumpkin bread pudding
directions: Combine bread cubes, raisins or dates and 1/3 C nuts.
Place in a greased 2 qt shallow baking dish.

title: italian roast beef
directions: Mix together and pour over meat.
Roast for 4 hours or until done.
Take out fat and bone.
Pull meat apart with fork.
Serve on hard rolls.

title: chiliburgers
directions: Cook onion and ground beef; drain.
Add rest of ingredients. Heat until cheese melts.
Spoon on hamburg buns.

title: diet ranch dressing
directions: Stir salad dressing mix and mayonnaise together with whip; fold in yogurt and mix well.
Chill.
Makes 1 1/2 cups of dressing, approximately 16 to 19 calories per tablespoon.

title: zucchini bread a la jo rigsby
directions: Grease two 5 x 9-inch bread pans.
Grate zucchini and set aside.
Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add oil, sugar, grated zucchini and vanilla.
Mix until blended.
Stir in nuts.
Divide batter between pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add oil and sugar.
Beat well, then add combined dry ingredients and vanilla, then add zucchini.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Pour boiling water over oats.
Add shortening, molasses and salt.
Dissolve the yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Add to cooled mixture.
Add the beaten eggs and flour.
Knead 5 minutes.
Place in greased, covered bowl in warm place.

title: crazy cake
directions: Place milk and pudding in saucepan and cook until thickened. Pour into large bowl and while pudding is still hot, pour in cake mix as it comes from package.
Mix well.

title: grandma's cake that won't last
directions: Combine eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla in mixer bowl; beat well. Add flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon; mix well.
Stir in pineapple, bananas and pecans.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan for several minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.

title: chow chow
directions: Grind tomatoes first and drain in colander.
Mix all ingredients together and simmer gently 40 minutes.

title: 24 hour marinated slaw
directions: Spread cabbage and thinly sliced onions in flat pan; sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar over all. Combine all other ingredients for the dressing and bring to a boil. Pour over cabbage. Store in covered container (airtight) in refrigerator for 12 to 24 hours. Keeps a month.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and garlic.
Add remaining ingredients.
Season with seasoning salt, dash of Tabasco sauce and 1 packet taco seasoning.
Serve with Fritos or corn chips. Top with grated Cheddar cheese, sour cream and guacamole.
(You can also substitute ground turkey for ground beef.)

title: make ahead pie crust
directions: Blend
flour,
sugar and salt.	Add shortening and work pastry with
hands.
Add	water,	vinegar and egg.
Work with hands until
mixed
well.
Roll
out portions on well-floured surface and well floured pin.
Makes pastry for 2 double crust 10-inch pies +.
Time of preparation: 20 minutes.

title: norwegian christmas cake
directions: Grease bottom of a 10-inch spring-form pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, with a mixer at high speed, beat eggs and 1 cup sugar until light and foamy, about 7 minutes.
Stir in 1 tablespoon water.
Add flour, cornstarch and baking powder, stirring utnil blended.
Pour batter into a pan and bake 35 to 45 minutes until done.
Cool cake on wire rack for 5 minutes and remove cake from pan.

title: fudge
directions: Mix cheese and sugar well.
Melt chocolate with water.
Add chocolate to cheese and sugar.
Plus add flavoring (vanilla or almond).
Pour in shallow pans and cool.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats; let stand for 20 minutes.
Mix all ingredients.
Add oats.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° until done.

title: creamy french dressing(a most pleasant recipe we've used for years.)
directions: Mix and chill at least 2 hours ahead so flavors blend.

title: sugarless apple pie(diabetic)
directions: Sift together flour, cinnamon and salt.
Add thawed apple juice, stir and heat until thickened.
Add sliced apples.
Pour apples into unbaked pie shell and dot with oleo.
Add top pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then turn oven to 350° and bake for 30 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix and pour
onto
top
of
chicken mixture. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until lightly brown.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Butter baking dish.
Sprinkle chops with salt and pepper.
Melt butter in skillet or heat oil.
Add onions and pork chops.
Brown lightly on both sides.
Place sliced potatoes in baking dish and arrange chops on top of potatoes.
Add soup and milk to onions in skillet and blend until smooth.
Pour over chops, cover and bake at 350° for about 1 hour, or longer for thick chops.
Uncover and cook until potatoes are tender.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain off fat.
Add Prego sauce, salt and pepper.
You can add some mushroom pieces if you wish. Simmer, uncovered, for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cook noodles in salt water with a little vegetable oil.
Drain and rinse.
Place half of noodles in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread with half of meat mixture, then sprinkle some Lawry's seasoning salt on, then half of Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, or until cheese is golden brown.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix melted butter, 1/3 cup sugar and pretzels together and bake at 400° for 10 minutes. When you remove it from the oven, let it cool.

title: green jello salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk over double boiler or microwave. Pour mixture over jello. Add the rest of the ingredients, gently folding in whipped cream last.
Garnish with nuts.

title: creamy icing
directions: Melt butter in small pan.
Add brown sugar.
Stir well, boiling 2 minutes on low fire.
Add milk; bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from fire.
Wait until it cools off so it will spread easily on cake.
Cut in 1-inch squares.
Enjoy.

title: pizza bake
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together.
Cook noodles.
In a large deep baking dish, layer the ingredients with the noodles first. Add pizza sauce, hamburger mixture, pepperoni and cheese.
Do this until all the ingredients have been used.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Great with garlic bread!

title: no-cook play dough
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add oil and boiling water.
Stir until mixed completely.
Knead with hands.
Cool completely. Store in refrigerator in resealable plastic bag.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Soak apples and bananas in pineapple juice while fixing celery, grapes and nuts, then drain and mix all ingredients with mayonnaise.

title: banana crush punch
directions: Mix water and sugar together until sugar dissolves.
Put bananas in blender and blend well.
Add the rest of ingredients, except soda.
Put in freezer until firm.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Separate eggs; beat whites until stiff.
Cream Crisco, butter and sugar.
Add yolks, then add flour, salt and soda sifted together.
Add nuts, vanilla, coconut and buttermilk.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in 3 (8-inch) pans for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, and syrup thoroughly. Add the margarine, coconut, pecans and oatmeal. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 375
degrees for 45 minutes.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with 20 Ritz crackers, crushed and mixed with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: cottage cheese waffles
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Set aside.
Beat eggs, milk, vegetable oil and vanilla together.
Add cottage cheese and beat until smooth. Combine with flour.
Cook in waffle iron.

title: cracklin' bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift meal and salt.
Stir in water and cracklings.
Melt butter in a 9-inch cast-iron skillet.
Pour in batter and spread over melted butter.
Cook for 25 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cut in wedges or break into pieces to serve.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add 7-Up.
Drain pineapple and add to Jell-O mixture.
Add marshmallows and bananas.
Cool until firm.
Mix pineapple juice, sugar, flour and egg.
Cook until thick; add butter and spread on the Jell-O.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix well. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes in greased and floured loaf pan or cake pan.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook beef and onion in frying pan over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until beef is brown; drain.

title: chicken sauce for the grill
directions: Blend onion and celery and add other ingredients.
Baste on chicken
and
watch
carefully on grill.
Will burn easily. Baste until chicken is done.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Beat together first 3 ingredients.
Mix next 5 ingredients and add to first mixture.
Add apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Run all except tomatoes through food chopper (quite fine) and simmer until soft.
Peel and cut up tomatoes.
Place in large kettle.
(I use an old pressure canner.)
Cook about 40 minutes and add the vegetables.
Mix well and season with salt and pepper in the can.
I can this in pint jars and add 1/2 teaspoon salt and a shake of pepper to each can.
Process in hot water bath for 35 minutes.
This makes a sort of chunky sauce.
I use it in goulash with canned tomatoes; it gives a very good tasting dish.
I started making this sauce because we liked it better than the sauces you buy in the store.

title: curried chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, water chestnuts, grapes, mandarin oranges and celery.
In a small bowl, stir mayonnaise, curry powder, soy sauce, lemon juice and salt to taste.
Mix well.
Stir dressing into chicken mixture.
Chill up to 8 hours.
Serve on a lettuce leaf.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Mix 2/3 of melted margarine and 2/3 stuffing with all ingredients.
Place in greased casserole.
Top with remaining stuffing and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, until browned.

title: e z potato soup
directions: In a large saucepan, place potatoes, onion and 2 c water-bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.

title: steamed shrimp
directions: For 1 pound
shrimp,
in an excessive amount of water, place bay leaf, pickling spice,
vinegar
and salt.
Cook for 10 minutes or until pink.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream margarine and cheese well; add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Press dough onto cookie sheet.
Cut into thin strips and bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: potato chowder
directions: In large saucepan melt margarine.

Saute onion, celery, green pepper, carrot and garlic about 3 minutes until crisp and tender. Add water, potatoes, soy sauce, thyme, basil, salt and pepper. Bring to boil, cover, simmer 20 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Add tomatoes.
Cover, cook 15 minutes longer.
(If tomatoes are acid add sugar.)
Makes about 12 cups.

title: frosted almond twists
directions: Grease cookie sheet very well.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Unroll crescent dough onto cutting board and cut each piece in half along straight perforations.
With fingers pinch diagonal perforations together on all pieces.
Cut each rectangle lengthwise into 6 strips.
Twist 2 strips together like a rope.
Cut each rope in half.
Place ropes about 1-inch apart on cookie sheet.
Brush each strip with egg and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 8 to 12 minutes until golden.
Remove from sheet immediately.

title: barbecue lemon chicken
directions: Mix together ingredients, except chicken. Marinate chicken several hours. Sprinkle generously with lemon pepper while barbecuing over low heat. Turn chicken often to prevent burning.

title: citrus fruit dessert
directions: This no fat, high-vitamin winter treat requires planning.
You also must peel and section citrus fruit.

title: pumpkin ginger squares
directions: Combine first four ingredients and mix well until crumbly, using electric mixer at low speed.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Combine the next seven ingredients and beat well.
Pour onto baked crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Combine last three ingredients and sprinkle over baked pumpkin filling.
Return to oven and bake 15 to 20 minutes or until filling is set.
Cool in the pan.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix in boiler, sugar, cornstarch, salt, Karo and water.
Cook until thickens; mixture will be clear.
Add jell-O.
Cool the hot mixture.
Fill pie crusts with fresh whole strawberries.
Cover berries with mixture.
Refrigerate.
Cover with Cool Whip before serving.

title: grandma keller's cinnamon flop
directions: Cream the butter and sugar; add remaining ingredients.
Place in 2 greased pie plates.
Sprinkle a small amount of cinnamon and brown sugar on top.

title: reuben bread
directions: In a
large bowl, sprinkle yeast over warm water;
stir until dissolved.	Blend
in
potato flakes, brown sugar, salt, caraway seed, oil and sauerkraut.
Gradually add flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead on floured surface until smooth, about 4 minutes. Place in
a greased bowl.
Cover; let rise in a warm place until double
in	size.
Punch
down;
shape into loaf. Place in greased loaf pan.
Cover;
let rise about 45 minutes. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until done.

title: dawn's potato chowder
directions: Cut up bacon and cook in deep pan.
When lightly browned, add onions, celery and garlic to bacon and saute until onions are clear.
Add chicken broth, potatoes, carrots, parsley and bay leaves.
Simmer until potatoes and carrots are fully cooked.
Add half and half and heat (try not to let boil).
Add instant potatoes to thicken to desired consistency.
(Start by adding about a cup at first.)

title: cheese cake
directions: Soften cream cheese in a large bowl; beat until fluffy.
Mix sugar, flour, salt and vanilla.
Add eggs and egg yolks, one at a time.
Stir in cream.
Pour into 10-inch spring-form pan and bake at 500° for 12 minutes. Don't open oven. Reduce temperature to 200° and bake for 1 hour.
(Mine always takes 1 1/2 hours.)

title: coconut-nut topping
directions: Use oven-glass batter bowl or mixing bowl (2 quart).

title: easy cobbler
directions: Put margarine in 12 x 13-inch pan and melt in oven.
Mix sugar, flour and milk together.
Pour 2 cups of fruit and juice over batter.
Bake until golden brown.

title: blitz torte cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add other ingredients in order given. Beat well and pour into buttered and lightly floured two layer cake pans.

title: apple turnovers
directions: Place apples in a bowl; sprinkle with lemon juice.
Add margarine.
Combine sugar, cinnamon and cornstarch; mix with apples and set aside.

title: egg pie
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl and mix well. Pour in deep pie shell or 2 shallow pie shells.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: jeanette's banana punch
directions: Mix and bring to a boil the sugar and water.
Cool.
Mix together the remaining ingredients.
After mixing the above ingredients, freeze.
Thaw until mushy; add 2 quarts ginger ale.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium-high and cook 5 minutes or until cranberry skins pop; cool.
Serve with meats.

title: mule ears
directions: Cream shortening and brown sugar.
Add eggs and mix well. Stir in molasses.
Sift together dry ingredients and gradually add to creamed mixture.
Chill dough 1 hour.

title: potato beef casserole
directions: Mix raw hamburger with onion, salt and pepper.
Press into a greased 13 x 9-inch dish.
Cover with condensed soup.
Sprinkle cheese on top of soup.
Place potatoes on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours (until potatoes are done).

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt into mixing bowl.
Add sugar, brown sugar, eggs, shortening and vanilla.
Blend, then mix thoroughly about 1 minute.
Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop from teaspoon onto an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Break egg into blender.
Add vinegar, salt, mustard and 1/4 cup of the oil.
Cover; turn on to lowest speed.
Immediately remove center of cover and pour remaining oil in a steady stream. Whip until thick, about 15 to 30 seconds.
Makes about 1 1/4 cups. Make 1 batch at a time; do not double.

title: crepes
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, milk, eggs, oil and salt; beat with a rotary beater until blended.
Heat a lightly greased 6-inch skillet; remove from heat.
Spoon in about 2 tablespoons batter; lift and tilt skillet to spread evenly.
Return to heat; brown on one side only.
To remove, invert over paper toweling.
Repeat with remaining batter to make 12 crepes, greasing skillet occasionally.

title: hot wings
directions: Season wings and fry like you normally do. Drain wings on paper towel; absorb as much grease as you can. While the first batch of wings are frying, start the sauce.

title: rum cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Sprinkle nuts in bottom of tube pan.
Combine remaining ingredients in bowl.
Blend and beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes or until cake pulls away from sides of pan.

title: bisquick easy egg and sausage puff
directions: Mix all ingredients and cover; refrigerate.
Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 2-quart casserole.
Pour mixture into casserole. Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 1 hour. Serves 6 persons.

title: two cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
This dough can be divided and used by adding different ingredients in each batter.
Choice of fruit, chocolate chips, nuts, coconut or anything you like can be added.
Drop by teaspoon on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: bacon and egg bake
directions: Mix all together, except bacon.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle bacon over top.
Bake for 20 minutes in 350° oven. Serve on toasted English muffin halves or baking powder biscuits.

title: pork normandy
directions: In large skillet, melt butter over medium-high heat.
Add pork cutlets, half at a time.
Cook until browned and remove.
Add apples; saute 1 minute.
Stir in water and sauerbraten mix. Stirring constantly, bring to boil.
Return pork to skillet. Reduce heat.
Simmer, partially covered, stirring occasionally, 10 minutes or until pork is tender.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: brownies
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pollo ai capperi(chicken with capers)
directions: Cut the chicken in pieces.
Dry the pieces, then flour them. Let them become golden in a pan with olive oil, butter and garlic. Add crushed rosemary, parsley and anchovies.
Make cook, adding little by little the cup of white wine.
When the chicken is almost cooked, cover the pieces with capers and the chunks of tomato. Serve hot with a side dish of boiled potatoes.

title: old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream the butter or margarine thoroughly, then gradually add sugar.
Combine the dry ingredients and add them to the butter, sugar mixture, alternately with the sour cream.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Turn out the dough onto a floured board.
Knead it and roll it out as thin as possible.
Cut into desired shapes.
Bake on a cookie sheet in a hot 350° oven until lightly browned.
(The cooking time depends on how thin you roll the cookies, so watch them carefully.)

title: ginger-soy drummettes
directions: Place chicken drummettes in gallon size Ziploc bag.
Mix remaining ingredients in small bowl; pour over chicken in bag. Seal bag and shake gently to coat chicken with marinade. Refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight.
Remove chicken from bag; reserve marinade.
Grill chicken over medium-hot coals or broil 6 inches from heat source until chicken is browned and juices run clear when chicken is pierced, 15 to 20 minutes.
Turn chicken halfway through cooking time and brush frequently with sauce.

title: best beer bread
directions: Pour into well-greased and sugared loaf pans.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Very good.

title: sunflower seed cakes(makes about 15 cakes)
directions: Place sunflower seeds, water and salt in a large saucepan. Cover and simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Put the mixture through
a food mill or puree in a blender.
Mix in the corn meal, a tablespoon at a time, to make a dough stiff enough to be shaped with the hands.
Cool at room temperature.
Shape into firm, flat cakes about 3 inches in diameter.

title: party punch
directions: Mix together.
Cool.
Put ice cubes in it.
Garnish with orange pieces and lime pieces. Makes 100 servings.

title: mississippi caviar
directions: Mix together and serve as a dip with corn chips.
Will keep a long time in the refrigerator.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and set aside 1 cup for top.
Mix all ingredients.
Put in greased and floured pans.
Top with 1 cup crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple butter pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat the egg until thickened and a lemon color.
Add apple butter, melted butter, spice, sugar and flour. Stir well to blend.
Add evaporated milk; mix well.
Place in unbaked pie shell and bake at 375° on the rack below the center of oven until filling is set and custard is golden brown.
After 40 minutes, remove from oven and cool on rack.
Serve topped with whipped cream.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease and flour two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Sift dry ingredients and pecans together and set aside.
In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Add oil, lemon peel, vanilla and lemon juice.
Beat briefly.
Stir in dry ingredients, then add zucchini and stir to blend.
Batter will be thick.
Spoon into loaf pans and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes on wire rack, then turn bread out of pans to cool completely.
Freezes well.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: mom's barbecued sauce(for over pork chops in oven)
directions: Salt and pepper to taste and add enough water to cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta.
Drain and cool. Cut up black olives, broccoli and other veggies.
Add to pasta and pour all of Italian dressing into mixture.
Mix together.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix bread crumbs, sage and onion soup together (dry).
In casserole dish, alternate layer of chicken, bread crumb mixture, chicken soup, mushroom soup and celery soup.
Top with layer of crumbs.
Reserve some chicken soup to spread on top of crumbs. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 400°.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Cook zucchini and onion in oleo until tender, about 10 minutes.
Stir in parsley and other seasonings.

title: margaritas
directions: Combine all ingredients in a shaker with crushed ice. Pour into martini glass rimmed with salt.

title: chop suey
directions: Cook onion in 1 stick butter for 3 minutes; add celery, salt, pepper and hot water.
Cook 5 minutes and add bean sprouts and meat.
Cook for 5 minutes.
In separate bowl mix cornstarch, water, soy sauce, gravy sauce and sugar and add to mixture.
Cook 1 minute.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal, milk, corn, onion, eggs, baking powder, and margarine.
Pour half of the mixture into skillet.
Sprinkle cheese, add jalapenos and sausage on top.
Pour remainder of batter over cheese, jalapenos and sausage.
Cook.

title: old-fashioned macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Layer one-third of macaroni in a lightly greased 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with one-third cheese; repeat procedure and top with remaining macaroni.
(Reserve remaining cheese.)
Combine milk, eggs, salt and pepper; pour over macaroni and cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and sprinkle with remaining cheese and paprika.
Cover and let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs.
Add corn and then gradually add flour, sugar and milk. Pour into a 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes or until puffed and golden.

title: dried apples and dumplings(schnitz un knepp)
directions: Wash apples.
Cover with water and let soak overnight or for a number of hours.
In the morning, cover ham with cold water and boil for 3 hours.
Add apples and water in which they have been soaked and continue to boil for another hour.
Add brown sugar. Prepare dumplings.
Drop by spoonfuls into the hot liquid with ham and apples.
Cover kettle tight and cook dumplings for 18 minutes. Serve piping hot on large platter.
Yield:

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Save 6 cherries with stems for garnish. Remove stems and pits from all other cherries.
In 2-quart saucepan, stir water and cornstarch until blended.
Add cherries, lemon peel, cinnamon, 1/4 to 1/3 cup sugar (depending how sweet cherries are) and salt.
Over medium heat, cook cherries until soft and mixture thickens and boils, stirring frequently.
Spoon cherry mixture into custard cups.
Mix flour, powder, oil, egg, 1/4 cup sugar and 1/8 teaspoon salt until blended.
Spoon batter on top of cherry mixture.
Bake 15 minutes or until top is golden.
Serve with drop of whipping cream and garnish with cherry.

title: lazy man's barbecue chicken
directions: Clean and cut up chicken.
Salt and pepper all pieces and place in oven or toaster oven.
Broil chicken until both sides are browned.
Remove from heat.
Pour barbecue sauce in large frying pan or Dutch oven.
Let it come to a boil, then place chicken on top of sauce.
Turn heat to medium and let chicken simmer for about 5 minutes.
Turn chicken and let simmer for another 5 minutes.
Turn heat on low and cook for about 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is done.
Turn periodically while cooking.

title: funnel cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add milk.
Sift half the flour with the salt and baking powder.
Add egg mixture.
Beat the batter smooth and add only as much flour as needed.
Batter should be thick enough to run through a funnel into deep hot fat.
Spirals and endless intricate shapes can be made by swirling and crisscrossing while holding funnel spout with finger.
Fry until golden brown. Repeat with next funnel of batter.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool. Dust with powdered sugar. Cut into squares.

title: apple upside down gingerbread
directions: Melt butter in bottom of a 9 inch square cake pan.
Combine brown sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle on bottom of pan.
Arrange apples on brown sugar mixture.
Prepare gingerbread mix as directed and pour over apple slices.
Bake as directed on gingerbread mix.
Invert on serving plate.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: grandma braunschweig's custard
directions: Put in blender; blend all of the ingredients.
Pour into a casserole; sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Put hot water in a frying pan; place casserole in the frying pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until a knife comes out clean.

title: big choca-chip cookies(chewy)
directions: Mix flour, soda and salt; set aside.
Stir together the sugars and butter until soft.
Use mixer.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well. Stir in flour mix.
Add chocolate chips.
Drop onto silver (light) cookie sheets (use ice cream scooper).
Bake at 300° for 22 to 24 minutes.

title: texas chili
directions: Brown steak pieces (in batches) and onion in margarine in large saucepan over medium heat.
Pour off drippings.
Add tomatoes with liquid, steak sauce and chili powder.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 1 hour and 15 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally.
Garnish as desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: angel food refrigerator cake
directions: Heat 2 cups milk; add egg yolks, beaten lightly.
Cook until thickened.
Cool.
Add gelatine dissolved in cold water.
Add pineapple, stiffly beaten egg whites and whipped cream.
Stir all together.
Break cake in small pieces and line bottom of dish. Add the filling, then another layer of cake and then the filling again.

title: pasta carbonara
directions: Gradually add milk to salad dressing and garlic.
Cook, stirring constantly, over low heat until warm.
Remove from heat; blend in eggs.
Add fettucini; mix lightly until noodles are coated.
Add remaining ingredients and mix lightly.
Garnish with additional chopped parsley, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Lay 2 cans of crescent rolls flat and press edges together in pizza pan or cookie sheet with sides.
Bake according to directions.
Let cool.

title: grandmother's italian bread(100 years old)
directions: Mix all ingredients together with warm water.
Knead 10 minutes.
Make ball.
Let rise for 20 minutes.
Punch down and divide into 9 loaves.
Let rise again until double in size.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes or until brown.

title: apricot-rice pudding
directions: Combine rice and 1 1/2 cups milk in a pan.
Heat to boiling; cover, remove from heat and set aside.
In a large saucepan, combine the remaining milk and half and half.
Beat the eggs and add to the pan.
Stir in sugar and salt.
Heat through.
Add vanilla.
Place reserved rice in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan; top with apricots and carefully pour warm egg mixture over the top. Place the pan in a large baking pan, filled with 2 inches of hot water.
Bake 1 hour,
or until set.
Sprinkle brown sugar over the top during the last 15 minutes of baking.
Serve warm or cold. Serves 10 to 12.

title: sausage roll-ups
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix Bisquick mix and water until soft dough forms.
Beat 25 strokes.
Smooth dough into ball on floured cloth-covered board.
Knead 5 to 8 times.
Roll dough in rectangle, 15 x 9-inches.
Brush with margarine.
Mix cheese and Italian seasoning.
Sprinkle over buttered pastry.
Cut dough into 15 (3-inch) squares.
Place a sausage on each square.
Roll up. Pinch dough to seal.
Cut each roll into 3 pieces.
Place seam side down on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake approximately 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Can be served as is or arranged around a dish of your favorite mustard and served with toothpicks.

directions: Mix

Butter tops.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Mix gently and let stand, refrigerated, overnight.

title: cookie sheet nachos
directions: Spread out and arrange the whole and mostly whole chips on a cookie sheet.
Place a teaspoon helping of refried beans on each chip making sure top is flat for rest of ingredients.
Spread out diced peppers evenly over chips.
Sprinkle cheese over nachos and bake at warm until cheese is melted.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and place in baking dish. Mix butter (melted) with flour and buttermilk. Pour over chicken in baking dish and bake until done and light brown on top, 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mushroom burgers
directions: Mix together; shape into patties and brown in skillet in 1 tablespoon margarine.
After browned, blend in the rest of soup with 1/4 cup of water.
Pour over patties.
Cover and cook over low heat for 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: sauce for grilled or baked fish(sauce for one pound of fish)
directions: Heat and pour over fish.
Cook 20 minutes.

title: brunch egg casserole
directions: In bottom of greased 10x6x1 3/4-inch baking dish, combine croutons and cheese.
In a bowl, combine eggs, milk, and seasonings.
Mix until blended.
Pour over crouton mixture in baking dish.
Cook 4 slices of bacon until crisp, drain and crumble.
Sprinkle over the top of casserole.
Bake in 325 degree oven for 55-60 minutes or until eggs are set.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Set aside pineapple. Place pineapple juice in a glass measuring cup.
Add enough water to measure 1/2 c.
In a small bowl combine juice, vinegar, sugar, ketchup, soy sauce and cornstarch; mix until well blended.
In a large skillet, heat oil and fry green pepper. Add sauce, cook until mixture boils and thickens.
Stir in chicken and pineapple; mix lightly.
Serve over rice.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating at least 2 minutes after each addition.
Add flour, salt and mace. Add extracts.
Bake in well-greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Melt 1/2 of margarine and cheese together to make sauce.
Mix vegetables and sauce in casserole.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Melt other half margarine and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Spread pecans in roasting pan.
Dot with butter and drizzle with syrup.
Roast at 250° for 1 hour, stirring often.
Spread on wax paper.
Salt generously.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Fill 4 quart jars with cucumbers, then fill with water.
Pour off water in pan and add 1/4 cup salt and bring to a boil.
Pour over cucumbers and add a pinch of alum to each jar and seal.

title: hawaiian chops
directions: Lightly grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place chops/chicken in and coat each piece with chopped onion, thick coat of barbecue sauce and cover with brown sugar.
Drain pineapple and place on top.
Cover lightly (do not seal edges) and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Delicious served with wild rice.

title: picante onion soup(makes 6 servings)
directions: Place onions, garlic and butter in 3-quart saucepan. Cook over medium-low heat about 20 minutes, stirring frequently, until onions are tender and golden brown. Stir in tomato juice, broth, water and 1/2 cup picante sauce. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes. Ladle soup into bowls and sprinkle with croutons and cheese.
Serve with additional picante sauce.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies very fine and set aside.
Cream together butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix pudding with the 3 1/2 cups of milk in another bowl.
Fold cheese mixture and pudding mixture together and add whipping topping.
Layer cookies and mixture, with last being cookies.

title: pina colada punch
directions: Chill all the above.
Slowly combine the sherbet with the juices, add the crushed pineapple and 7-UP in punch bowl and serve.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: To Tint:
Dilute few drops of food coloring with 1 teaspoon water.
Add to 2 cups coconut!
Toss with fork until all tinted.

title: million dollar salad
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk with lemon juice.
Add fruit cocktail, pineapple, pecans and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Make this the day before you are to serve it.
Keep in the refrigerator.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Place in 2-quart casserole. Top with cheese and almonds.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve spiced peaches as an accompaniment.
Perfect luncheon or buffet casserole.

title: pineapple dip
directions: Combine
cream	cheese and pineapple (liquid, too) in a bowl. Blend until smooth.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening and white sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla to mixture.
Add, after sifting together the flour, soda and salt.
Mix in oatmeal, nut meats and potato chips.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
A delicious crisp cookie.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into casserole dish; bake until firm and light brown on top in 350° oven.

title: pasta with tomatoes, black olives and capers
directions: In a large pot of boiling salted water, cook pasta until tender, about 10 minutes.
Drain well.
Return pasta to pot.
Add olive oil, garlic, tomatoes, olives, capers and parsley.
Cook over medium heat, tossing frequently, 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and serve.

title: oven jambalaya
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a lightly greased 3-quart baking dish.
Cover and bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Slice sausage in 1/2-inch slices.
Stir in sausage and shrimp.
Cover and bake an additional 20 minutes.
Makes 10 servings.

title: wheat free carrot cake
directions: Mix all together except egg whites.
Fold them in last.
Bake at 375° for 55 minutes or until done.

title: marble cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Grease and flour bundt pan. Cream softened butter and sugar; adding one egg at a time. Beat until creamy. Add lemon and vanilla extract. Mix all dry ingredients together. Add to above mixture alternating with buttermilk. Mix well. Scoop out 3 large spoonfuls of batter and mix with chocolate syrup. Put white batter into pan. Pour chocolate batter on top. Mix lightly with spoon. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: sponge candy from buffalo, ny
directions: Butter or oil an 8 in. square tin, set aside.
Put sugar, vinegar, syrup and water in a heavy saucepan (cast iron if you have it).
Be careful that your pot is big enough, because sugar has a tendency to boil over.
Gently heat the mixture, stirring with a wooden spoon, until sugar has dissolved and syrup has melted.
Bring to a boil, cover and boil for 3 minutes, then uncover and boil until temperature reaches 300° F on a candy thermometer.

title: easy stroganoff
directions: Brown beef and onion in 2 tablespoons fat in deep skillet, stirring occasionally.
Place beef in greased casserole.
Arrange noodles over beef.
Stir Worcestershire sauce, celery salt, salt and pepper into tomato juice; pour over noodles.
Simmer, covered, for 25 minutes or until noodles are tender, stirring occasionally. Stir in sour cream.
Sprinkle with parsley before serving. Yields 6 servings.

title: mozzarella meat pie
directions: Brown meat.
Drain. Add onion and celery; cook until tender. Add tomato sauce, 1/2 cup cheese and seasonings; mix.
Separate rolls into 8 triangles and place in 9-inch pie plate, pressing together to form crust.
Flute edge.
Fill with hot meat mixture and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix first three into a large bowl until thick. Pour into pie crust. Refrigerate for 1 hour or until set. Makes 6 servings.

title: baked corn
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and mix well. Salt and pepper to taste. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: bean salad
directions: Put into large mixing bowl; toss with two wooden spoons. Transfer to a bowl with a lid that fits tight.
Let set overnight in cool place or in refrigerator.
Toss again before serving.

title: peach cookie sundae
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; stir into sliced peaches.
Pour into a square 9-inch baking dish.
Top with 1/4 inch slices of cookie dough.
(May use your favorite cookie recipe.)
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until golden brown.
Let cool.
Serve with ice cream.

title: hot chicken salad(serves 4)
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in a greased casserole. Sprinkle crushed potato chips over top.
Bake 30 minutes in a preheated 300° oven.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer the ingredients in a clear casserole dish.
(Put mayo and sugar mixture, then cheese last.)
Refrigerate for 2 hours prior to serving.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix in bowl the flour, sugar and salt.
Heat oleo, water and cocoa until boiling point.
Pour hot mixture over dry ingredients, then add sour cream and soda.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and let jell.

title: snack pizza
directions: Brown pork; drain.
Over low heat, add cheese, catsup, garlic and oregano.
Heat until cheese melts.
Spread on party rye and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: sweet revenge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 300° (do not attempt to bake at a higher temperature or they will burn).
Generously grease 8 x 12-inch baking pan. Combine chocolate and butter in medium saucepan. Melt over medium-low heat, stirring constantly, until the chocolate is nearly melted.
Remove from heat and stir until smooth.

Whisk in the white sugar until blended, followed by the eggs, one at a time, the flour and the vanilla. Fold in the mini-marshmallows and 1 cup chocolate chips. Pour into prepared baking pan and smooth evenly. Sprinkle the remaining 1/2 cup chocolate chips on top. Bake for 53 to 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Do not overbake!
Cool to room temperature or freeze. Makes 48.

title: lemon curd
directions: Add eggs to mix.
Mix all ingredients together.
Cook gently over low heat until thick, but still falls easily from spoon.
Do not boil or let mixture separate.
Cool; store in jar in fridge.

title: gooey butter coffee cake
directions: Blend cake mix with 1 egg and melted oleo.
Pat into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Beat together 2 eggs, very soft cream cheese, and powdered sugar.
Pour over top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
While hot, sprinkle with powdered sugar or crushed nuts.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat soft margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder and cinnamon.
Stir well.
Add oats, applesauce and raisins.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes (I bake them 15 minutes).
Makes 60 good size cookies. Use tablespoon to drop dough on nonstick cookie sheets.
Store in airtight container.

title: slops
directions: In olive oil, saute peppers, onions and meat in saucepan until veggies are tender and meat is brown.
Add tomato sauce and seasonings.
Cook 1 hour until everything is soft.
Boil noodles according to directions.
Mix together.
Add cheese on top.
Add noodles to your own taste.

title: batter rolls
directions: Heat milk and margarine together.
Bring to a scalding level (do not boil).
In a large bowl, add sugar and salt.
In a small bowl, pour in lukewarm water.
Add yeast to lukewarm water.
Let stand until yeast is soft (about 10 minutes).
Pour milk and margarine mixture into large bowl with sugar and salt.
Let set until mixture is lukewarm.
Add beaten eggs, mix well.
Add yeast. Stir in wheat bran.
Add 5 1/2 cups flour.
Let dough rise 2 hours.
Stir down with spoon, about 3 times, while dough is rising.
Spoon bread dough into greased muffin tins.
Let rise 2 hours.
Bake about 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown at 350°.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Cut eggplant into 1 1/2-inch cubes and remainder of vegetables into large chunks.
Combine all ingredients.
Place in dish; add butter.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter and jelly muffins
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; make a well in center of mixture. Combine sugar and next 4 ingredients; beat at low speed with an electric mixer until blended. Add to dry ingredients; stir just until moistened. Spoon batter into 24 miniature muffin cups coated with cooking spray, filling half full. Top each with 1/4 teaspoon jelly and top with remaining batter. Bake at 400° for 12 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Remove from pans immediately and let cool on a wire rack. Yield: 2 dozen muffins.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Lightly oil a baking dish.
Place chicken breast halves in dish and put green pepper strips on top.
In small saucepan, combine ketchup, vinegar, soy sauce, sugar and 1/2 cup water.
Mix cornstarch with 1/4 cup water and when the ketchup mixture boils, add the cornstarch mixture.
Cook 1 minute, then pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Chill.
Roll into small balls.
In double boiler, melt chocolate chips and paraffin. Place toothpick in balls and dip in chocolate mixture.
Drop on wax paper.
May need to rewarm chocolate to keep it thin.
Keeps very well in refrigerator in airtight container.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Grease baking sheet.
Place in warm oven.
Combine peanuts and baking soda in bowl, tossing to coat.
Combine sugar, salt and butter in large skillet.
Cook over medium heat until sugar melts, stirring constantly.
Add peanuts, tossing to coat.
Spread in thin layer on prepared baking sheet.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: wassail punch
directions: Mix all ingredients for 10 minutes.
Remove cinnamon and cloves.
Serve hot from percolator or punch bowl.

title: red pepper dip
directions: Process ingredients in food processor, grinding walnuts first.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine and cheese together; add other ingredients. Bake until moisture is dissolved, but not dry.
Can be mixed ahead of time and refrigerated until ready to be baked.

title: orange fruit mold
directions: Add enough water to fruit juices to make 3 cups.
Heat to boiling.
Add water to the jello; stir until dissolved.
Chill until almost set.
Combine coconut, marshmallows, sour cream, pineapple and oranges.
Add to jello.
Put into large mold and chill for several hours, until firm.

title: blondies
directions: Melt shortening, then add brown sugar.
Mix well and cool. Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Add chips and nuts.
Pour on greased cookie sheet and spread evenly.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pan, then cut in squares.

title: saucy sausage
directions: Cut peppers and onions (long strips).
Boil sausage until almost done.
Saute peppers and onions in margarine; set aside.
In large pot, start to warm spaghetti sauce.
Cut sausage into bite size pieces, adding into sauce.
Add peppers and onions.
Cook on medium heat 5 minutes, stirring often.
Cut Mozzarella cheese into thin, small strips.
Add to sausage mixture and return to medium heat for 1 minute.
Serve and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: jemima's old-fashioned yellow cake with lemon glaze
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth.
(May take 5 to 10 minutes if butter is cold.)
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour, salt, vanilla and lemon extract; beat well.
Pour in a 10-inch greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box.
Add 1/4 cup oil. Pour half of batter into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt caramels and evaporated milk together. Pour over hot cake.
Sprinkle chips and pecans on top.
Pour on remaining batter.
Bake for 30 minutes or more.
Ice with your favorite chocolate icing.

title: easy pork chop casserole
directions: Place potatoes in baking dish, salt and pepper.
Place pork chops on top, cover with soup and water.

title: amazing chicken and dumplings(weight watcher)
directions: Bring broth to a rolling boil, put flour on both sides of the tortillas; using all the flour.
Cut tortillas into 1 1/2 inch pieces, drop in boiling broth.
Reduce heat and simmer in a covered pot.
Let simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in chicken and milk until heated thoroughly.
Let stand off heat 10 minutes covered. Serves 4.

title: whipping cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening.
Add sugar and cream well. Add eggs one at a time; beat well.
Add flour and vanilla.
Add whipping cream and beat until light and fluffy.
Put in cold oven in large tube pan.
Cook 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: quick and easy cookies
directions: Generously sandwich peanut butter between crackers, then dip into melted chocolate.
Lay on wax paper to cool.
Chocolate can be melted in glass dish in microwave.
Delicious!

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil zucchini until partially tender.
Drain and slice. Prepare Stove Top according to directions on box.
Add other ingredients to stuffing mix.
Add zucchini and put all into greased casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cracker salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves or in a hulled out tomato or bell pepper.

title: strawberry jam with green tomatoes
directions: Put green tomatoes through blender twice.
Mix all ingredients well.
Bring mixture to a rolling boil and boil for 20 minutes.
Pour into jars and refrigerate.
Can use any flavor jello.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add bananas and mix well.
Add egg and dry ingredients and vanilla.
Beat well.
Bake in greased paper-lined loaf tin at 350° for 50 minutes.
This freezes well.

title: meat ball stew
directions: Mix beef, egg, onion and salt; shape into 24 meat balls.
Brown in shortening in a skillet; pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serves 6.

title: grasshopper
directions: Mix all 3 in blender.
Store in freezer.

title: chestnut soup
directions: Peel the outer rind from the chestnuts and place them in a large pan of warm water.
As soon as this becomes too hot for the fingers to remain in it, take out the chestnuts, peel them quickly and immerse them in cold water.
Put them in a pan and cover them with the stock to stew gently for about 45 minutes or until they break when touched with a fork.
Puree the chestnuts; add salt, cayenne pepper and mace, stirring until it boils.
Add the cream. Serves approximately 4.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Slice tomatoes thin and cook in vinegar and a bit of water until tomatoes are tender.
Add sugar, butter, cinnamon and cornstarch.
Simmer until slightly thickened.
Pour into pie crust.
Cover with pastry.
Punch a few fork holes in top of crust.
Sprinkle crust with sugar and a bit of cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Crush should be golden brown.

title: coconut orange balls
directions: Combine all ingredients and shape into balls.
Roll in coconut.

title: garlic green beans
directions: Mix ingredients in small saucepan for 20 minutes.

title: graham cracker bars
directions: Line bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with graham crackers. Set aside.
Combine butter and sugar.
Mix egg and milk; add to sugar mixture.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs, pecans and coconut.
Spread over whole crackers.
Top with remaining whole crackers.
Spread with frosting.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: broccoli soup(thick and delicious)
directions: Saute onion in margarine; stir in rest of ingredients and bake in ovenproof dish at 300° for 3 hours.

title: cold corn dish
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: chocolate marshmallow cake
directions: Cream the margarine, cocoa and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time; beat well.
Add flour, nuts and vanilla.
Mix by hand.
Pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
As soon as cake comes out of oven, cover with marshmallows.
Let melt for about 5 minutes.
Spread icing on cake.

title: p-nut butter pie(kids love this one!)
directions: Mix 8 ounces Cool Whip, pudding and milk.
Add peanut butter. Pour into baked pie shell( a chocolate crust is really good).
Top with 4 ounces of cool Whip and 1 tablespoon peanut butter.

title: quick cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix cinnamon and sugar.
Dip each roll in melted butter, then in cinnamon-sugar mix.
Place in pans.
Bake according to directions on rolls.
Remove from oven.
Loosen rolls immediately.

title: fluff
directions: Mix instant pudding with fruit (use juice).
Fold in marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: dot's 3 day coconut cake
directions: Make cake according to directions.
Make 2 (8-inch) layers. Split to make 4 layers.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes and add margarine, salt, pepper, soup, onions, sour cream and cheese.
Put into a 3-quart casserole and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften to room temperature; cream until smooth.
Mix thoroughly with the pineapple, green pepper, onion and salt.
Roll in the pecans; serve at room temperature.
Makes 2 cup size balls.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Saute onions in butter until golden brown.
Mix meat in a bowl and add onions, salt, allspice and pepper.
Mix well.
Soak bread in some cream and add to meat mixture with eggs.
Add rest of cream and water slowly and mix well.
Form into one inch meat balls.
Saute in oil or butter and brown evenly on medium to high heat. Be sure to shake frying pan continuously to retain shape of meatballs.
This should take 8 to 10 minutes.
Don't crowd in pan, do a few at a time.
Serve on a warm platter with party toothpicks or on a bed of rice.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Slice onions and cook until clearish looking in the sausage grease.
In a large bowl, mix together soup, pimentos, seasoned salt and then add onions and sausage.
Put in 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased pan.
Add grated cheese on top, then crumbled crackers, and then pour melted margarine over the top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: christmas salad
directions: Drain pineapple; add water to make 1 cup; boil.
Add to lime jello.
Add crushed pineapple and 2 teaspoons lemon juice.
Pour into a 13-inch pan.
Let set.
Dissolve lemon jello using 1 cup water (boiling).
Blend cheese and mayonnaise.
Whip jello until light and fluffy.
Add cheese mixture.
Pour over first layer. Chill.
Dissolve raspberry jello in 2 cups hot water.
Chill partially.
Pour over 2nd layer.
Chill.
Cut in squares.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: cheesy meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium mixing bowl; blend thoroughly.
Spread mixture evenly in a glass loaf dish.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave at power level "High" for 18 to 20 minutes or until center is no longer pink when fork or knife is inserted.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes before serving.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, strawberries, Jell-O, cornstarch and salt in medium saucepan.
Stir in boiling water.
Bring mixture to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 3 minutes.
Cool completely.
Arrange berries in baked pie shell.
Pour glaze over berries.
Chill several hours.
Top with whipped topping and cream.

title: ice cream
directions: Cook on low sugar, flour, salt, 2 c. whole milk, egg yolks until thick.
Add to churn and add evaporated milk, sweet condensed milk and fill remaining with whole milk.
Add sweetened fruit of desired.
Churn until ready.

title: imitation crab salad
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.	Chill.

title: confetti corn and bulgar salad
directions: In large bowl, combine bulgar, garlic, water and oil. Mix well with fork and let stand 30 minutes.

title: chilled seafood lasagna with herbed cheese
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Put 4 noodles in baking dish.
Add half of all ingredients, then layer the other half of ingredients. Put in refrigerator.

title: squash puppies
directions: Cover sliced squash with water, cook over medium heat 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain well.
Mash and drain again. Combine squash with remaining ingredients.
Drop mixture by tablespoons into hot oil (350°).
Fry 5 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Brown chicken in hot oil in large skillet.
Add peppers, carrot and garlic; cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with soy sauce.
Add to pan with pineapple and juice, vinegar, sugar and ginger.
Bring to a full boil.

title: corn souffle
directions: Mix together corn, flour, sugar, salt, pepper and milk.
Add egg yolks to mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into corn mixture.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole and dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: easy oven stew
directions: Mix all together and bake 5 hours at 275° or 6 to 8 hours at 250°.

title: low-fat angel food dessert
directions: Beat cream cheese and gradually add milk, then Cool Whip. Beat until smooth.
Stir in vanilla.
Break cake into small pieces.
Put layer of broken pieces in large glass dish.
Spread cream cheese mixture over cake.
Spread pie filling on top. Refrigerate overnight.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Fry hamburger done; drain grease.
Mix cream of mushroom soup with hamburger.
Line bottom of bread pan with potato puffs. Sprinkle cheese over potato puffs, then spread hamburger mix over cheese.
Bake for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix in saucepan the sugar, cocoa, milk and oleo.
Put on medium heat and cook until it starts to boil.
Remove from heat. Cool for 1 minute. Add vanilla, salt, peanut butter and oatmeal. Stir well. Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Cool.

title: washington favorite apple pie
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and spices. Sprinkle over sliced apples in large bowl.
Toss until well coated. Spoon into pastry shell. Blend 1/2 cup sugar, 1/2 cup flour and 1/2 cup margarine. Sprinkle over apples. Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Drain cherries and pineapple.
Add juices to water; bring to a boil.
Pour over Jell-O; stir well.
Add everything, etc.
Keep stirred until set.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: cheese broccoli
directions: Saute chopped onion and celery in butter.
Break up broccoli into small pieces.
Put rice over broccoli, onions and celery. Pour soup and cheese mixture over all.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: salmon ball
directions: In medium bowl, drain and flake salmon.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well with fork.
Shape into ball and roll in parsley flakes.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving with your favorite crackers.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large jar and turn until evenly pink.

title: pink salad
directions: Heat juice from pineapple. Add Jell-O. Cook slightly and add crushed pineapple, buttermilk, Cool Whip and nuts. Chill and serve.

title: marcia's oriental slaw
directions: DRESSING:
Mix together flavor packets from noodles, vinegar, oil, sugar, and set aside.

title: cherry pie
directions: Mix together cornstarch, sugar and water; bring to boil.
Add cherries.
Cook slowly 10 minutes.
Remove from heat; add Jell-O. Stir until dissolved.
Pour into pie shell.
Cool.
Cover with topping.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make in a ball.
Roll in pecans.
Best if made a day before and refrigerated overnight.

title: chocolate cookie sheet cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together twice. In saucepan, put oleo, water and cocoa and bring to a boil. Pour this over the dry ingredients. In another bowl, put eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla; add to the other mixture and mix well. Bake in greased and floured shallow cake pan or cookie sheet 20 minutes at 350°.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix in a saucepan sugar, cornstarch, salt, vinegar, margarine and 1/3 cup liquid, drained from beets.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add beets.
Let simmer 10 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Add celery and onion, saute for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir and mix together.
Pour in a 3-quart casserole and cover.
Bake for 2 hours at 350°.

title: strawberry ice cream (cooked custard)
directions: Combine 2 cups of milk and the marshmallows in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until all marshmallows are dissolved.
Gradually stir about 1/4 of this hot mixture into the well beaten eggs.
Add the remaining hot mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook until the temperature reaches 165°.
Remove from heat; add the remaining 2 cups of milk, sugar, half and half, heavy cream and the vanilla.
Chill.
Combine this thoroughly chilled mixture with the pureed strawberries (chilled, also). Pour into a 5-quart hand-turned ice cream freezer and freeze according to directions.
Let ripen 1 hour before serving.
Makes about 1 gallon.

title: veal scaloppine a la marsala
directions: Dip the veal scallops in flour and shake off excess.
Brown the veal in heated oil on both sides and remove to a warm platter. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Drain most of fat from pan.
Add wine and scrape any residue from bottom of pan.
Return to a boil. Add butter.
When sauce thickens, lower heat and return veal to pan.
Heat through and serve with sauce.
Serves 4.

title: florentine soup
directions: *Gordon's Food Service has this.

title: good punch
directions: Mix everything together, except ginger ale, beforehand.
Chill completely.
Add ginger ale right before serving.

title: acini de pepe salad
directions: Boil acini de pepe in boiling salted water until done.
Cool under running water.
Drain fruit.
Combine juices, sugar, eggs and flour.
Cook until thickened.
Cool.

title: six cup fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and put in refrigerator.
This keeps well and is easy to make.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Combine chicken, minced onion, salt, pepper, poultry seasoning and water.
Bring to a boil; cover and simmer until chicken is cooked and tender.
Remove chicken from broth.
Bone chicken.
If necessary, add water to broth to make 6 cups.
Return chicken to broth and bring to a boil.
Combine flour with ice water to make soft dough.
Knead gently 30 seconds.
Tear off small pieces and drop into boiling broth.
Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: caramel rolls
directions: Place rolls separately in well-buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle pudding over the rolls.
Mix brown sugar and melted butter together and pour over rolls.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Let rise on counter overnight.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Take out and turn upside-down immediately.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onion and salt until tender (very little water). Drain.
Add soup, eggs and milk.
Mix well until blended; pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Melt butter; crumble in saltines. Sprinkle on top of squash.
Bake approximately 40 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pepper steak
directions: Pound steak to 1/4-inch thickness. Cut into 1/4-inch wide strips. Sprinkle meat with paprika and allow to stand while preparing other ingredients. Using large skillet, brown meat in margarine. Add garlic and broth. Cover and simmer 30 minutes. Stir in onions and peppers.
Cover and cook 5 minutes more. Blend cornstarch, water and soy sauce. Stir into meat mixture. Cook, stirring until clear and thick (2 minutes). Add tomatoes and stir gently.
Serve over rice.

title: cheese muffins
directions: Mix flour and baking powder.
Add 1 cup cheese to mixture; set aside.
Mix egg, butter, cayenne pepper and milk together.
Stir into flour and cheese mixture with fork.
Spoon 2/3 full into greased muffin tins and sprinkle with remaining cheese on top of each muffin.

title: fish tacos
directions: Cook bacon and set aside.
Fry fish and flake.
Add bacon, tomatoes and onions and saute until vegetables are softened.
Roll in warm tortillas.

title: cabbage and noodles
directions: Boil large pot of water and add egg noodles until almost done. Drain noodles and set aside.
Chop the cabbage into small pieces. Melt margarine in large skillet; add cabbage and cook until browned.
Add noodles, salt and pepper.
Mix well until done.

title: royal brunch crepes
directions: Combine eggs and salt, beating well. Add flour alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Mix well after each addition. Add 1/4 cup melted butter; beat well.
Refrigerate batter 1 hour (this allows flour particles to swell and soften so the crepes are light in texture).
Brush the bottom of an 8-inch crepe pan with melted butter.
Place the pan over medium heat until butter is just hot, not smoking.
Pour about 3 tablespoons batter into pan; quickly tilt pan in all directions so batter covers the pan in a thin film. Cook about 1 minute.

Lift edge of crepe to test for doneness. Crepe is ready for flipping when it can be shaken loose from pan. Flip crepe and cook about 30 seconds on the other side (this side is rarely more than spotty brown). Stack crepes between layers of waxed paper to prevent sticking. Set aside 18 crepes; freeze the remaining crepes for other uses.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Sprinkle rice in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Lay chicken on rice (skin side down).
Sprinkle onion soup over chicken.
Pour soup and water over chicken and rice.
Seal tightly.
Bake 2 to 2 1/2 hours at 400°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: fried venison round steak
directions: Lay meat on a cutting board and make cuts every 1/4-inch on each side, sideways and lengthways.
Do this on both sides of the steak, but only cut in about 1/3-inch of the width of the steak. Heat a skillet to medium-hot with 1/2 stick of butter for grease. Don't let the butter burn.
Take each steak and lay on the back of your hand. This will spread open the knife cuts.
Sprinkle flour and salt and pepper over each side and fry until brown on each side.
Serve immediately after removal from skillet.
Take 1/4 cup of water and pour into the skillet, stir with contents of the skillet and serve like gravy over rice or potatoes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix spaghetti with remaining ingredients.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt. When well blended add water and mix until dough forms a ball. Roll half of the dough very thin and cut into 2-inch strips. Line the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with the strips.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: magic meatballs
directions: Combine chili sauce, jelly and lemon juice in 2 quart saucepan.
Shape beef and salt into 1-inch balls.
Place in sauce and cook, simmering 30 minutes.
Serve hot with toothpicks.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Drain pineapple.
Mix all ingredients together and chill until set.

title: corn salad
directions: Cook corn and add other ingredients.
Stir in sour cream until it melts.

title: hanky panky
directions: Brown sausage and ground beef; drain.
Cut Velveeta into cubes and mix with meat mixture; melt.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir thoroughly.
Spoon onto party rye slices.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
Store in plastic bag until ready to eat.
Heat at 325° to 350°.

title: peanut bars(quick)
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 pound salted peanuts.
In microwave, melt butter, peanut butter chips and milk.
Stir well; add marshmallows.
Pour on top of peanuts and press 1/2 pound peanuts on top.
Cool.
Cut in squares.

title: fudge pudding
directions: Mix in order given. Bake in buttered pan (9 x 9) in pan of water for 30 to 40 minutes in 325° oven. Let cool. Serves 9.

title: walter's legendary lentil soup
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon butter in heavy Dutch oven over medium heat. Add ham; cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add 6 cups stock, lentils, chili and savory.
Cover and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer until lentils are tender, but firm to bite, stirring occasionally, for about 30 minutes.
Heat oil in heavy large skillet over medium heat.
Add onions, carrots and bell pepper; stir until vegetables begin to soften, about 5 minutes. Add garlic; cook 2 minutes.
Stir mixture into soup; add enough stock to cover.

title: hot sandwich
directions: Fill 16 sandwich or hot dog buns.
Wrap each tightly in foil. Store in refrigerator several hours or overnight.
Heat just before serving in 425° oven 15 minutes.
Nice for club or parties.

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt hash browns in microwave and break them up, then set aside.
Mix Cheez Whiz, butter and milk and onions (chopped) in pan and melt on low heat.
After mixture is melted, add sour cream and hash browns.
Put in Pam coated Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until brown around edges and on top.

title: nut roll
directions: Mix all ingredients together and add more flour if needed for a soft dough.
Let raise about 2 hours.
Divide in parts.
Roll out one at a time and dab with melted butter.
Sprinkle with sugar, 3 handfuls, and cover with 1/2 cup ground nuts.
Roll into long rolls and bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 25 minutes, until light brown.

title: sweet 'n sour chicken
