directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Add garlic and carrots.
Saute briefly; add green peppers and saute briefly.
Add bouillon, soy sauce, vinegar, sugar, ginger and pineapple with juice.
Bring to a full boil.
Thicken with cornstarch to make a good sauce.
Serve with Minute rice.

title: butterscotch pie(recipe of mrs. turley noland, a past president)
directions: Cook butter and brown sugar until rich brown; add scalded milk and simmer until sugar is dissolved.
Whip in yolk of 1 egg, beaten with 1 tablespoon of cornstarch.
Bake until custard is set.
Make meringue, whipped with 1 tablespoon of powdered sugar

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Cut chicken breasts in half, then cut in half again and pound flat.
Place 1 slice of ham and 1 slice of Swiss cheese on chicken and roll up.
Do this until all chicken is rolled. Dip chicken in butter.
Mix Italian bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese together and roll chicken in the bread crumb mixture.
Place chicken, seam side down, in a shallow baking pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Make Sauce while chicken is baking.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Wash and quarter tomatoes.
Place in large kettle.
With potato masher, mash as much as possible.
Chop finely the onions, celery, peppers and tomatoes.
Add seasonings; bring to boil. Simmer until most of liquid has evaporated.
Mixture is like thick cream, then press through cone (can take hours!).
Makes 10 1/2 pints.

title: filipino fresh lumpia
directions: For the stock, boil the shrimp shells in 1 1/2 c. water. Saute the garlic, onions, ground pork, shrimp, and tofu.
Add the potatoes and 1/2 c. stock. Cook for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add the beans and cook for another 5 - 10 minutes. Then add turnips, soy sauce, vegetable oil, salt and pepper (to taste), and fish sauce.
Continue to stir and cook for 5 more minutes.
Drain and save the broth for the dipping sauce.
Allow the mixture to cool.

title: texas fudge
directions: Layer in 9 x 13-inch casserole pan.

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; add onions, sliced very thin.
Cook until golden brown, then add broth or stock and salt and pepper.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Place potatoes and carrots (if desired) in casserole dish. Crumble meat and add soups. Add onion. Cover and bake 1 1/4 hours.

title: cinnamon flop
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add milk alternately with flour and baking powder.
Put batter into greased and floured pan.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake for 30 minutes.

title: homemade canned milk
directions: Mix ingredients by hand or mixer until well blended. Makes approximately 14 ounces.

title: cheese hash brown potato bake
directions: Butter 9 x 12-inch dish.
Combine all ingredients (except cheese) and pour into pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Top with cheese.
Bake to melt.

title: weather warmer
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan; blend well and bring just to
a boil.
Serve hot.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: classic potato salad
directions: In large bowl, stir together first five ingredients until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients; toss to coat well.
Cover; chill.
Makes 5 cups.

title: thin white sauce
directions: Melt butter or fat.
Blend flour or seasonings until smooth. Add milk gradually, stirring constantly, until starts to boil. Cook 3 minutes.
Cook vegetables according to directions; drain and serve with sauce if desired.
A thicker sauce may be made by adding more flour and fat.

title: chocolate cherry bars
directions: Mix cake ingredients together by hand; batter will be stiff. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or an 11 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Cool 10 minutes.
Frost with Fudge Glaze.

title: hot tea mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 2 cups mix.
For 1 serving, combine 2 tablespoons mix with 1 cup boiling water.

title: faye's overnight fruit salad
directions: Drain over bowl: oranges, pineapple and fruit cocktail.
Use juice plus water to make 1 1/2 cups liquid.
Mix liquid and pudding mix.
Cook until thick.
Cool.
When cool, add fruit plus marshmallows and whipped cream.
Stir all together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Add bananas before serving.

title: sour cream mini muffins
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake in greased mini muffin tins at 450° for about 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Best when eaten immediately.
Easy to reheat in microwave.

title: marinated pork tenderloin
directions: Combine sherry, soy sauce and brown sugar. Rub over meat and marinate overnight in refrigerator. Roast at 300° until tender (approximately 90 minutes). Makes 6 servings.

title: sloppy joe
directions: Brown burger and onion.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer 20 minutes.

title: banana candle
directions: Stick banana in hole of bagel.
Cut hole in lettuce leaf and stick lettuce leaf onto the banana.
Stick the slice of pineapple on the banana.
Eat and enjoy!

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In medium bowl, beat egg yolks with sweetened condensed milk, lemon juice and food coloring.
Bake 30 minutes.
Cool.
Top with whipped cream.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: sweet-sour cucumbers
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, water, salt, pepper and parsley.
Pour over cucumbers and chill.

title: raspberry poke cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package, baking in well-greased and floured 9 x 13 inch pan at 350 degrees for 30 - 35 minutes.
Cool in pan 15 minutes; then poke with fork at 1/2 inch intervals.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water and spoon over cake in pan.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Top with thawed Cool Whip when serving.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients in a bowl.
Mix the last 3 ingredients.

title: onion rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add to 2 cups flour, sugar and salt.
Knead.
Knead in additional 1/2 cup flour.
Let rise until doubled in size.
Knead again.
Roll out in rectangle.
Add 1 small chopped onion; roll up.
Slice about 1-inch thick.
Rise again (about 45 minutes).
Brush with egg and bake for 15 minutes at 425°.

title: christmas tree preserver
directions: Mix together and keep tree stand filled.

title: fruit jello
directions: Combine jello and boiling water and allow to jell until slightly set.
Add the thawed raspberries, diced bananas and chopped nuts.
Pour into a square baking Pyrex dish.
Refrigerate . Cut in squares to serve.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In medium bowl, thaw strawberries.
Add eggs and oil.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
Add strawberry mixture and nuts; stir until just blended.
Grease and flour 2 bread pans.
Fill each bread pan 3/4 full with batter.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes (until toothpick comes out clean).
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.

title: nacho chicken tortillas
directions: Step 1:
In a 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, combine soup, chicken, tomatoes and chilies; heat thoroughly.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugars, vanilla and eggs.
Mix flour, soda, baking powder and salt and add to first mixture.
Add oatmeal. Bake at 425° until brown.

title: cabbage and potato bake
directions: Place shredded cabbage in large baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Layer potato and onion slices.
Add other seasonings of choice.
Top with chicken breasts.
Salt and pepper.
Seal dish with foil.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: ranch pretzels
directions: Break pretzels into bite size pieces.
Mix package of dressing with oil and pour over pretzels.
Bake in roasting pan for 1/2 hour at 250°.

title: cooked cheese
directions: Mix together baking soda and cottage cheese.
Set several hours or overnight.
Cook on low heat all ingredients until smooth.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Steam broccoli.
Mix all the rest and pour over broccoli in buttered dish.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Serve at once or it sets up.

title: ham and glaze
directions: If desired, score ham and stud with whole cloves.
Place ham in baking pan.
Add 1/4 cup water; cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: quiche(great for breakfast or anytime)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread crescent rolls out in pan, pinching perforations together.
Cut sausage links in half lengthwise and lay, flat side down, covering crescent rolls, or use diced ham evenly spread over rolls. Sprinkle cheese over the meat layer.

title: ziti bake or lazy lasagna
directions: Make pasta according to package directions; drain.
Set aside. In same pot, cook meat until well browned.
Preheat oven to 350°. Remove pot from heat.
Stir in Ricotta, Parmesan, parsley, egg, salt, pepper and 1/2 of sauce.
Mix together and stir in pasta. Toss gently to coat.
Spoon into 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Pour remaining sauce evenly over pasta mixture.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella.
Bake 20 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pizza dough
directions: Combine hot water, sugar, salt and oil.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast over 1/4 cup warm water and stir until dissolved.
Add yeast to lukewarm water-sugar mixture.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour and beat until smooth.
Add enough additional flour to make a stiff dough.
Place in a greased bowl and brush top with oil.
Cover and let rise in a warm place, until double in bulk, about 45 minutes.
Divide in two equal parts.
Roll and stretch each into a 13-inch circle.
Place on greased pizza pans.
Top as desired.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: potato yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 c. warm water.
Mix next 5 ingredients in bowl.
Stir in yeast mixture; add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Chill in refrigerator covered for 2 hours.
Shape into rolls in baking pan.
Let rise in warm place 2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: dumplings
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Cut in shortening with knife or finger tips.
Add milk to make a soft dough.
Dough is dropped a tablespoon at a time on chicken or meat stews the last 15 to 50 minutes of cooking.
The kettle must be covered closely and cover must not be removed during cooking.

title: curried broccoli soup(makes 7 cups)
directions: Cut off the flowerets in bite size pieces.
Coarsely chop stems.
Set aside.
Bring 1 cup of chicken broth to a boil in a 1-quart saucepan; add half half of the flowerets and boil, uncovered, for 3 to 4 minutes.
Drain, saving broth.
Cool; cover and chill broccoli.
In the same pan, melt the butter over medium heat; add onions and curry and cook until limp.
Stir in broccoli stems, remaining flowerets and remaining broth.
Cover and simmer 12 minutes until tender.
Cover and chill.
Ladle into small bowls and top with cooked flowerets.
Pass sour cream and peanuts.
Makes 7 cups.

title: cheese cake
directions: Leave cream cheese out overnight to soften.
Cream the cheese, sugar and eggs until nice and creamy.
Add vanilla.
Line spring-form pan with graham cracker crumbs.
Pour cream cheese mixture over graham cracker crumbs.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Combine sour cream and 1/4 cup sugar and pour over cheese cake that has been baked.
Cook another 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool.
Place in refrigerator for 6 to 8 hours. May garnish with strawberry glaze.
I just serve cherry or strawberry pie filling on the side.

title: double chocolate cheers
directions: In saucepan, combine milk, candies and cocoa.
Bring just to a simmer.
Place in blender and process until smooth.
Serve hot, topped with whipped cream.
Garnish, if desired, with additional candies.
Makes one serving.

title: party parmesan appetizers
directions: In small mixing bowl, cream butter.
Beat in cheese until light and fluffy.
Gradually beat in flour and sour cream.
Stir in caraway seed.

title: texas trash
directions: She lived in a house where help was not hired.

title: honey-glazed chicken wings
directions: Cut off and discard wing tips. Cut wings in half at joint. Place wing pieces in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Combine honey, soy sauce, oil, fresh ginger root, scallions, catsup and minced garlic in a small bowl.
Pour mixture over wing pieces, turning to coat. Cover and chill 1 hour.
Transfer wings to a lightly greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 45 minutes, turning once.
Transfer to a serving platter.
Yields 8 to 10 appetizer servings.

title: kielbasa and red cabbage(polish style)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except sausage.
Cover and microwave at Full power for 10 minutes, stirring twice.
Pierce kielbasa thoroughly and arrange on top of cabbage.
Cover and microwave at Full power for 13 to 15 minutes or until heated through.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes before serving.

title: yum yum casserole
directions: Cook beef in skillet and drain off fat.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, garlic and spices.
Cook and drain noodles according to package.
Add sour cream, cream cheese and onions to noodles and mix.
Place meat mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan; cover with noodles. Sprinkle with cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serves 8.

title: chewy cake
directions: Mix sugar, butter and eggs.
Add flour, vanilla and pecans. Mix well.
Pour in greased pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli in colander and set aside.
Combine beaten eggs, mayonnaise, soup and onions.
Mix well.
Add cheese and mix again. Then add broccoli, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well.
Turn into 2-quart casserole, sprinkle top with Ritz cracker crumbs. Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Do not cover.
Pork out!

title: cheese cake
directions: Melt butter, cinnamon and sugar.
Mix with crumbs and line the sides and bottom of 9 or 10-inch pie pans.

title: mary jo's chili
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer.

title: apricot glazed chicken(easy and delicious)
directions: Mix the three ingredients.
Pour over chicken breast.
Place in a 13x9-inch baking dish and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar. Add water and vanilla flavoring.
Add flour and nuts.
Chill for 1 hour.
Shape into balls or fingers.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for about 20 minutes.
Cool completely.
Roll in 4x sugar.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Put fresh strawberries into pie shell. In saucepan, mix water, sugar and cornstarch. Cook until clear and thick.
Add Jell-O. Pour over berries.

title: apple rings
directions: On 1st day, peel cucumbers and slice thick; take out seeds. Soak in lime water for 24 hours.
On 2nd day, drain and rinse; soak in ice water 3 hours 3 different times.
Then combine vinegar, water, food coloring and sugar and soak cucumbers overnight.
On third day, drain and add cinnamon sticks wrapped in cloth and red hots; heat well 30 to 40 minutes and pour over cucumbers; seal.

title: rhubarb nut bread
directions: Sprinkle 1-1/2 c. sugar over chopped rhubarb and let stand for 30 minutes.
Sift together the flour, 1 c. sugar, salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Stir in the milk, eggs, and oil.
Fold in the rhubarb and the nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 inch loaf pan and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix together and place in a casserole dish.

title: oriental salad
directions: Drain corn, beans and peas.
Combine all vegetables.
Heat vinegar, sugar and oil until sugar is dissolved.
Cool.
Pour liquid over vegetables. Cover container and refrigerate.
Serve as salad or side vegetable.

title: "those" potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes 1 day before until soft.
Drain and refrigerate overnight.
Peel next day and shred on large grater.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Place in greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes until brown and bubbly on top.
Don't cover. Serves approximately 15.

title: coconut refrigerator cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions in sheet cake pan.
While cake is still hot, prick all the way through with a fork.
Mix sugar and milk and let come to a boil.
Pour over hot cake.
Let cake cool.
Mix together Cool Whip and coconut and spread on top of cake.
Refrigerate.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes, until done.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Baking Temperature: 250°.
Baking Time: 1 hour.

title: polenta
directions: Cook polenta following package directions.
Pour on cutting board and let cool.
Cut into squares.
Arrange squares in buttered ovenproof casserole in layers.
Pour melted shortening and sprinkle Parmesan on each layer.
Bake in 350° oven until golden brown. Mangia!
Mangia!

title: freezer fruit salad
directions: Thaw and drain strawberries and peaches.
Combine cream cheese, salad dressing and sugar; beat until smooth.
Fold in strawberries, peaches, pineapple and marshmallows.
Whip cream and fold into fruit mixture.
Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Cover with freezer wrap and freeze. Thaw slightly, invert onto serving dish and slice.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken and add salt, pepper and chopped onion.
Take chicken out of the broth and remove meat from bones.
Boil spaghetti noodles in broth until done.
Add chicken.
Then add tomatoes and soup.
Spread in long pan and top with cheese.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: wild rice casserole(good stick to your ribs dish!)
directions: Brown sausage and drain. Add onions, peppers and mushrooms. Mix rice according to package. Add sausage and vegetables. Stir in soup. Stir in 3/4 cup of cheese. Top with remaining 1/4 cup. Use cooking instructions on rice box.

title: chicken wings in oyster sauce
directions: Use second and third joints only (use tips for soup).
Dry the wings, heat oil and brown wings, a few at a time.
When all have been browned, discard the oil. Return wings to wok with all the remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Remove cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally, until about only 1/2 cup liquid remains.
Serve hot or cold.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash cooked squash; add all the other ingredients.
Mix well. Pour into a greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: chow chow(a tasty accompaniment to any meat, fish or poultry)
directions: Put tomatoes, onion, green and red peppers through coarse blade of food grinder.
Combine with shredded cabbage in large kettle.
Dissolve salt in water.
Pour over vegetables and let stand overnight.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except egg whites.
Add beaten egg whites last.
Mix and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325°.
Pies will be thick.
Makes 2 large or 3 small pies.
Cushaw can be used instead of pumpkin.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Remove 2 crescent rolls and pinch together to form rectangle. Spread thin layer of sausage over roll.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Roll up very tightly.
Freeze.

title: stuffed eggplant italian style
directions: Cut eggplant in half; cut out insides and cook until soft. Mix all ingredients together.
Fill eggplant shells.
Place in tomato sauce to cover (no paste).
Cook in oven 20 minutes.

title: self-rising biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix shortening into flour.
Add milk while stirring dough with a fork.
Turn dough out on floured board.
Roll dough out to 1/3 to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with floured cutter.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet or pan. Bake 12 to 14 minutes or until brown.

title: candy turkeys
directions: For each candy turkey you'll need two vanilla wafers, one chocolate covered cherry, five pieces of candy corn, one burnt peanut candy, one chocolate chip morsel and approximately one tablespoon of chocolate frosting.

title: williamsburg black cherry salad
directions: Drain cherries and reserve 1 cup cherry juice.
Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup boiling water.
Add lemon juice, cherry juice and sherry.
Rinse 3-cup mold or 6 individual molds in cold water. Pour in cherry mixture and chill until partially set.
Add cherries and return to refrigerator until firm.
Serve on lettuce with French dressing or honey dressing.
Serves 6.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Mix white sugar, brown sugar, oil and eggs well.
Add cornflakes and oats to mixture.
Sift and add flour, soda and baking powder; mix well.
Add vanilla.
Drop on greased cookie sheet from teaspoon, allowing room to spread during cooking.
Bake about 8 minutes at 350°.
Do not overcook.

title: microwave rarebit(creamy cheese sauce served on toast.)
directions: In 4-cup glass measure, microwave on High the cheese and butter for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring every minute until smooth. Stir in salt, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and hot sauce.
Blend with milk and soup.
Microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring every minute until steaming hot.
Serve on toast.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Pour pudding mix into bowl.
Add small can of undrained pineapple; stir well.
Add mandarin oranges and pecans.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Cover; refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: beef 'n beet
directions: Slowly cook beef pieces with desired seasonings (ex: salt, onions, pepper, oregano, rosemary) until about half cooked (30 minutes on medium heat).
Add the root part of the red beets, washed and cut to pieces, about the size of the meat.
Cook together with meat until both are soft (about 30 minutes on medium heat).
Add to the beets and meat.
The beet greens torn into small pieces.
Simmer together on medium heat for about 10 minutes.
Greens will wilt.
Stir together for a colorful, tasty and healthful meal.

title: rosie hurt's butterscotch pie
directions: In large saucepan, combine flour, salt, brown sugar and beaten egg yolks with milk; stir until mixed (use a wire whisk).
Bring to boil over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened. Remove from heat, add butter and vanilla; mix well.
Cool and pour into a baked pie crust.
Make meringue with egg whites and bake. Cool.

title: green beans with garlic(4 servings)
directions: Stir together soy sauce, sugar and sherry or water and set aside. In a wok or wide frying pan, toast sesame seeds over medium heat until golden (about 3 minutes), stirring often. Remove from pan and set aside. Increase heat to medium-high and pour oil in pan. When hot, stir in garlic, ginger and beans. Cook stirring for 1 1/2 minutes. Stir in soy mixture, reduce heat, cover and cook until beans are tender crisp (about 7 minutes).

title: mario's spaghetti
directions: Add bouillon cubes to water.
Cook bacon until crisp, pour off 2/3 of grease and add vinegar.
Mix eggs with milk.
Cook spaghetti; drain.
Add milk mixture and the hot bouillon water. Mix bacon mixture with spaghetti.
Heat and mix in Parmesan cheese.
You can warm up later and add milk.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add egg, milk and vanilla. Mix well.
Add dry ingredients.
Refrigerate dough 3 to 4 hours. Roll into balls and dip in sugar.
Bake on greased cookie sheets for 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: crab vegetable soup
directions: Cook soup bone in water for 1 hour.
Add vegetables, potatoes, tomatoes and Old Bay.
Cook until vegetables are tender. Add more water if necessary and add Old Bay.
Take out soup bone and add crab meat.
Cook about 15 minutes more.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook until thick.
Add strawberries and pour into baked pie shell.
Top with whipped cream.

title: fruit fluff pie
directions: Drain all fruit.
Beat condensed milk and lemon juice together until well mixed.
Fold in whipped topping.
Mix well.
Add fruit and divide into pie shells and chill.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients.
Beat well.
Add all dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill a couple hours.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: calzones
directions: Roll out dough to cookie sheet size. Scatter spinach evenly. Layer cold cuts, and cheese. Roll Jelly Roll fashion. Length-wise and tuck in ends. Brush top with beaten egg. Bake at 350° for 25 min. Cool. Wrap refrigerate or freeze. Reheat at 320° for 20 min.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Pour all into blender and blend on medium speed until smooth. Pour into greased 10-inch pie plate and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Put black-eyed peas in strainer and rinse with water to remove salt.
Chop green onions, jalapeno peppers and bell peppers; add in amounts to suit own taste.
Mix all ingredients.
Can serve hot or cold.

title: fudge pie
directions: Sift together flour and cocoa.
Mix in sugar.
Blend butter, eggs and vanilla in a separate bowl.
Combine mixtures.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Place crescent rolls on a pizza pan (or cookie sheet) and spread and mash edges together to form crust.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: thunderbird wine punch
directions: Mix wine, limeade and club soda in punch bowl; add ice and sliced limes (optional).
Serve.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove from broth and cook noodles in broth until done.
Add vegetables and cream of chicken soup to noodles.
Cut chicken in small pieces; add to noodles.
Makes a good one dish meal.

title: jam strips
directions: Cream first 5 ingredients together.
Mix flour and baking powder together; add creamed mixture.
Divide dough in half. Press each half into long rectangular strips.
On one cookie sheet, put both halves lengthwise.
Using back of a spoon, press out a shallow indention in the center of each strip of dough.
Add jam into indention.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
When cooled, drizzle on Almond Glaze and cut into 1 1/2-inch bars.

title: tuna log
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Drain oil from tuna. Add tuna and onion to cream cheese.
Add
enough
oil from tuna to moisten. Shape into a roll. Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: chocolate-oat-nut-cake
directions: Stir
together	flour, salt, soda and cocoa; set aside. Put oatmeal in bowl, stir in boiling water and let stand about 10 minutes.
Stir
in	margarine
and brown and white sugars. Add eggs; mix well.
Beat in flour mixture and mix well.
Fold in 1/2 of	the chocolate chips and spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle
remaining chips and nuts on top.
Bake in preheated
oven
about
minutes.	Cool
in
pan. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: kontaifi dessert(an excellent dessert every time)
directions: Put contaifi phyllo spread in oval Pyrex dish.
Dot with the unsalted butter.
Place under broiler.
As it browns, turn it over and around and replace under broiler again until well, but golden brown.
Level it out in Pyrex and set aside.
Boil sugar and water for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and add 1 tablespoon lemon juice.
Pour this over the contaifi in Pyrex.
Now take 4 egg yolks and sugar with vanilla.
Beat until light yellow.
Take 5 cups of milk (pour 1/2 cup into small bowl and add the 8 tablespoons cornstarch and mix) and put remainder of milk into a large saucepan to slowly bring it to scalding.
When the milk is scalded or ready to boil, slowly add this to the cornstarch mixture which has been added to the egg yolk mixture.
Stir constantly.
Pour back into saucepan and stir constantly, until it thickens.
When thickened, pour over Kontaifi in the Pyrex dish.
Let cool.
Then put towel over it and cover with aluminum foil.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Early the next day, whip up to 1/2 kilo whipping cream and add 3 tablespoons powdered sugar.
Spread this whipped cream nicely over custard in Pyrex and replace in fridge.
Just before serving, sprinkle with 150 grams roasted, chopped almonds.

title: hot sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Shape into small balls.
Bake at 350° in a roasting pan with rack until brown, approximately 10 to 15 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Use muffin pan; cook for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Bring to a boil cranberries, sugar and water.
Cook until berries break open.
Remove from fire.
Add until they melt the jello and marshmallows.
Set aside to cool. Then add apples, celery and nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Beat all seasoning into egg.
Dip chicken parts into egg mixture and coat with cornflakes.
Place in baking dish; add stock to dish.
Cover tightly.
Place in preheated oven at 375°.
Bake, covered, for 1/2 hour, then uncovered for 1/2 hour.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk to 234° or soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add Fluff, peanut butter and vanilla; beat until smooth. Pour into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions and drain.
Add butter, cheese and dressing mix and add beaten eggs.
Let stand for a couple of hours to let crumbs absorb moisture.
Make into balls.
Put on cookie sheet and freeze.
Store in plastic bag. When ready to use, take out the amount needed, arrange on a cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: eclair lush
directions: Use a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix the pudding according to package directions.
Let sit for 5 minutes.
Line pan with grahams.
Fold Cool Whip into pudding.
Put layer of pudding on top of grahams. Add another layer of grahams, then rest of pudding.
Put third layer of grahams, then spread on the icing.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Grease bottom and sides of 2-quart casserole.
Place 3 cups cabbage in it.
Saute onion; add ground beef.
Heat through, but do not brown.
Spread on top of cabbage.
Add remaining 3 cups cabbage.
Top with soup, spreading to cover.
Bake in 350° oven until cabbage is tender, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: peas
directions: Fry bacon; crumble fried strips.
In bacon fat fry chopped green onions.
When tender, add flour.
Add chicken stock and peas.
Cook until peas are tender.
Sprinkle with bacon.
Serve.

title: holiday gelatin salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Cool for 20 minutes.
Add enough water to pineapple juice to make 1 cup.
Stir liquid into cream cheese until smooth.
Add cream cheese mixture to cooled jello.
Stir in pineapple and pecans; blend well.
Pour into square dish.
Chill until set.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Bring 1 1/2 quarts of water to boil.
Add rice and salt.
Cook until tender, stirring occasionally.
When rice is done, drain. Cool.
Cut shrimp lengthwise and set aside.
Heat oil in heavy skillet.
Stir in shrimp and onion.
Beat eggs and add to skillet. Stir and cook for 2 1/2 minutes.
Stir in rice and continue to cook for 3 minutes.
Sprinkle soy sauce and mix well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add bean sprouts and cook 3 more minutes. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: swiss and ham appetizers
directions: Combine ingredients, except cornflakes. Chill. Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in corn flakes. Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serve hot.

title: lemon cake
directions: Break cake into bite-size pieces in a 13 x 9 x 3-inch glass dish.
Mix Jell-O.
Cool.
Pour over cake.
Mix pudding.
Cool. Pour over cake and Jell-O.
Refrigerate.
Serve with or without Cool Whip.

title: roux(base for stews and gumbo)
directions: Mix flour and oil in a heavy pot (the heavier, the better). Have water heating.
Do not turn on heat under flour and oil until it is thoroughly mixed.
Stir constantly over medium heat. When the roux is a dark, rich brown, turn off heat and continue stirring.
Add heated water to lower temperature and stop browning.
Turn heat back on and add the rest of the ingredients for your stew or gumbo slowly.
Makes enough for 1 hen or 2 pounds of shrimp.

title: shrimp-crab bread salad
directions: Remove crusts from bread; spread lightly with butter.
Cut each slice into 20 small cubes.
Add onion and eggs.
Refrigerate overnight.
Add shrimp, crab meat, celery and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate for 3 to 4 hours.
Serves 8 to 12 people.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Pour marinade over carrots, onion and bell pepper.
Cover and refrigerate.
Flavor is better if prepared 1 day before serving.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Mash and mix with eggs, milk, butter, cinnamon and sugar.
Pour into casserole dish and bake for 20 minutes or until done at 325°.
Sprinkle with marshmallows and brown.

title: spinach dip
directions: In a medium bowl, stir spinach, sour cream, mayonnaise, soup mix, water chestnuts and green onions until well mixed. Cover and chill 2 hours. Serve with raw vegetables, chips or Triscuits. If desired, can be served in round bread, scooped out in center.

title: low-fat refried beans
directions: Heat liquid Butter Buds in a 10-inch nonstick skillet over medium heat until hot.
Add pinto beans; cook, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes.
Mash beans; stir in chili powder, cumin, salt and pepper.
Add more liquid Butter Buds to skillet if necessary.
Cook and stir until a smooth paste forms, about 5 minutes.
Garnish with grated Alpine Lace nonfat Cheddar cheese or Kraft Free cheese slices, melted on top.
Serves 4.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over the oats and let stand for 20 minutes. Meanwhile, cream the shortening with the two sugars.
Then beat in the eggs; stir in the cooled oats mixture.
Sift the flour and other dry ingredients together and add to the batter.
Stir in the nuts.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix together
the ingredients.
Mix together the following, then add to the first ingredients:

title: corned beef dip
directions: Combine all ingredients until well blended.
Cover and chill. Serve as a dip for raw veggies.
Yields about 3 cups.

title: creamed beets
directions: In a frying pan melt butter.
Add flour.
Cook for a minute. Add vinegar, hot water, sugar and seasonings.
Cook until the consistency of thick cream.
Add the beets to this sauce.
Lightly mix and cook for two minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: chocolate candy
directions: Combine sugar and milk.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add Marshmallow Creme, chocolate chips and vanilla. Stir well until creamy.
Pour into pan that has been buttered. Cool and cut.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Refrigerate overnight.
This can be a salad or vegetable dish.

title: taco wrap
directions: Mix sour cream, cream cheese, Ranch dip, olives and onion. Cover burrito skin; roll up and chill.
Cut in one-inch pieces. Serve with taco sauce.
Can be made ahead and kept in refrigerator.

title: orange spiced tea
directions: Mix all the above ingredients together. To serve, stir 2 heaping teaspoons of the mix into an 8 ox mug of hot water or a 10 oz glass of cold water. This drink is great hot or cold.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Drain and wash under cold water.
Cut up pepper and tomato into small pieces.
Add to drained spaghetti along with seasoning and Italian dressing.
Sprinkle in the cheese and allow to set overnight for best flavor.

title: clam chowder
directions: Put all ingredients into a large pot.
Let cook until celery and onion are cooked tender.
Include the juices from the cans of clams.
Do not add anything to the cans of soup.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix together, slice an orange thin and add to punch.
Add some maraschino cherries.
Serve with ice cubes.
Makes about 7 cups.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix together and spread on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Fill large roaster with salted popcorn.
Keep warm in oven.
Melt butter.
Add brown sugar and corn syrup.
Boil to 250° for 5 minutes.
Pour over warmed popcorn.
Mix well.
Bake 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Cool.

title: tuna roll-up
directions: With fork, stir cold water into Bisquick.
When soft dough is formed, roll out into rectangle, on floured board.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix well and store in large plastic container.
Boil water. Put 3 to 4 tablespoons of chocolate mix in cup and fill with the water.
Mix well.
Makes lots!!
Enjoy!!

title: peanut butter treats
directions: Combine butterscotch chips and peanut butter in a large saucepan.
Stir over low heat until smooth.
Remove from heat and add cereal.
Stir until well coated.
Press mixture into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in casserole sprayed with oil. Sprinkle top with bread crumbs or food yeast.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups of sugar, salt, flour, eggs, soda and crushed pineapple together.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Before baking, mix together brown sugar and nuts.
Sprinkle on top of raw cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box.
Pour half of mixture in a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels with milk over low heat to make a sauce. Pour over cake that has been baked.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour remaining batter over this and bake 17 to 20 minutes.

title: snickers torte
directions: Mix crumbs, sugar and butter together for crust.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Set aside to cool.

title: apple macaroon pie
directions: Butter a 9-inch pie plate and fill with sliced apples. Combine 1/4 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and sprinkle over apples.
Mix together remaining 1/4 cup of sugar, salt, flour, beaten egg and margarine.
Pour over apples (batter should be thick).
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in salted water until tender; drain.
Melt butter and add flour until well blended and smooth.
Add milk gradually, constantly stirring until mixture boils.
Add salt and pepper; cook for 3 minutes.
Stir in grated cheese and add the macaroni.
Serve.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil and egg until well blended.
Sift flour, salt and soda.
Add bananas to sugar mixture, then the flour and nuts. Mix well.
Grease and flour a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Pour batter into pan; bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy fruit dip
directions: Blend ingredients together.
Serve with fresh strawberries, pineapple, cantaloupe and watermelon balls.

title: swedish baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Leave just enough water in the beans so that you can see it.
Add brown sugar, molasses, onions, salt, bacon or salt pork, pepper and mustard.
Add bacon drippings. Bake at 325° until beans are done, approximately 5 hours.
If roaster cooks fast, reduce heat.
These beans are baked in a large electric roaster.
I cut this recipe in half for a smaller amount.
When cool, you can freeze them.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Prepare spaghetti; drain.
In medium bowl, blend milk and egg. Add spaghetti and toss to coat.
Spray a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan with vegetable cooking spray.
Spread spaghetti mixture evenly in prepared pan.

title: blue cheese ball
directions: Soften and mix together all ingredients.
Form a ball.
One hour before serving, roll in chopped pecans.

title: crock cheese
directions: Blend all ingredients well and pack in a crock.
Serve with crackers or bread sticks.
This is better if it is made several days before serving.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add well beaten egg.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add alternately with milk to the butter and sugar mixture.
Add blueberries.
Bake in greased muffin tins for 20 to 25 minutes. Yield: 12 muffins.

title: corn bread squares
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Add milk, eggs and oil.
Beat well.
Pour into 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 9 squares.

title: easy pie crust for open face pie
directions: Sift flour and salt into 9-inch pie plate.
Boil water and Crisco together; pour over flour and salt.
Mix with fork until flour is all wet.
Then pat out and flute edges with fingers.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Line a pan with cookies and slice 1 1/2 bananas over cookies. Add more cookies and bananas.
Repeat until all bananas and cookies are gone, making a crust on top with cookies.
Set aside.
Separate eggs; put whites in a bowl and set in refrigerator.
Beat yolks well and put in a double boiler.
Add sweetener and milk and whip well.
Set over medium heat; keep stirring until thick.
Add flavoring and pour over bananas and cookies.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar. Spread over banana pudding.
Bake at 300° until brown.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Butter a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Brown sausage and drain grease.
Cut edges off of bread; cut into squares.
Butter both sides of bread, then place in dish.
Spread small pieces of sausage over buttered squares; sprinkle grated cheese over sausage.
Beat eggs and milk together; pour over top.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: butterscotch supreme
directions: Mix flour, melted butter and 3/4 c. nuts.
Press into a 9 x 13 pan.
Cook 15 minutes at 300.
Cool.
Mix 8 oz. cream cheese (softened), sugar, and cool whip.
Spread over cooled flour crust. Mix pudding and milk, spread over cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining nuts.

title: eclair pudding
directions: To a large box of instant vanilla pudding, add 3 cups of milk and beat until no lumps.
Add the Cool Whip; mix together.
Take a pudding bowl and layer with crackers; set aside.
Mix sugar, cocoa and milk; mix real good.
Cook for 1 minute at a hard boil, stirring constantly.
Add butter while cooking, then pour over stack of filling and crackers.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers.
Cut in thin slices.
Peel and slice onions. Combine onions and cucumbers.
Add salt.
Let stand 2 hours. Drain.
Heat vinegar, water, celery seed, mustard seed, sugar, ginger and turmeric to boiling.
Add cucumbers and onions.
Boil slowly until tender.
Pack while hot
in freshly sterilized jars or let cool and pack into freezer containers for freezing or keeping in refrigerator.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Combine chopped chicken, cabbage (chopped) and green onion tops in large bowl; set aside.
Reserve the seasoning packs from noodle packs.
Place noodles in large bowl and crush coarsely.
Stir seed and almonds in with noodles.
Melt oleo in skillet.
Add noodle mixture and cook, stirring until toasted.
In another bowl, combine the flavor packs from noodles with sugar, oil, Accent, salt, pepper and vinegar.
Mix well.
Toss all mixtures together 20 to 30 minutes before serving.

title: black bass with oyster stuffing
directions: In a skillet, melt 1/4 cup butter. When hot, add 1 cup drained oysters. Watch out, they pop and spit a little. Turn until done (they will harden). Then dice. Add to prepared stuffing. Mix well.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Beat these ingredients together and add topping.

title: play dough
directions: Mix flour, salt and alum in a large container.
Combine water and the drink mix in a pan and bring to boil.
Add water to mix of dry ingredients and then add oil. Mix and knead until smooth. Store in an airtight container.

title: hot shrimp canapes
directions: Bake biscuits according to package directions.
Cool and split biscuits.
Leave on baking sheet.
Chop shrimp and combine with remaining ingredients, except sesame seed.
Spread mixture evenly on cut biscuit halves.
Toast sesame seed in dry frying pan over medium to low heat until light golden brown in color.
Sprinkle seed on canapes and broil until lightly browned and bubbly.
Serve while hot.
This is good to make ahead and broil at the last minute.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix altogether and form into small balls.

title: make-ahead breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until firm in center.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: elegant potatoes au gratin(servings:  4)
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets; cool, peel and shred, using medium grater.
Shred cheese with same grater.
Butter 2-quart casserole. Alternate layer of potatoes and cheese in casserole; sprinkle with salt.
Pour cream over potato-cheese layers.
Combine crumbs and butter; sprinkle over top.
Refrigerate, covered, several hours or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven until heated through (55 to 65 minutes).

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar together; set aside approximately 20 minutes, then add remaining ingredients. Mix well by hand. Pour into greased and floured oblong cake pan. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until
toothpick comes out clean. This batter will be quite thick.

title: coconut sour cream cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions, making two 8-inch layers.
Split both layers horizontally after they have cooled. Blend together sugar, sour cream and coconut.
Chill.
Spread all but 1 cup of sour cream mixture between the four layers.
Mix the one cup of mixture with Cool Whip and spread on top and sides. Seal in airtight container and refrigerate for 3 days before serving.
Keep refrigerated after cutting.
Will keep in freezer for several weeks.

title: dessert pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spread about 2/3 roll cookie dough on 13-inch pizza pan. Bake 10 to 15 minutes until brown.
Remove from oven and cool completely. Combine cream cheese and sugar, mixing until blended. Spread over cooled crust.
Arrange fruit on cream cheese mixture.
Chill. Cut into wedges or squares. Top with a glaze, optional.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: punch
directions: Boil sugar and 4 cups water; add Jell-O.
Mix other ingredients together and add to Jell-O liquid.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: frances' amazing coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients (except coconut) in blender.
Cover and blend on low speed 3 minutes.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate and let stand 5 minutes.
Then sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: prune cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease Bundt pan; set aside.
In large mixer bowl, combine all cake ingredients except walnuts.
Beat at low speed until all ingredients are moistened.
Increase speed to medium; continue beating until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool cake in pan just long enough until you can remove cake from pan.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Stir dry ingredients together thoroughly; mix in cherries (with liquid), eggs and oil.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Serve with whipped topping.
(Preheat oven to 350°.)

title: pineapple-cheese casserole
directions: Drain pineapple and save juice.
Mix pineapple and cheese. Mix flour, 6 tablespoons juice and sugar.
Add to pineapple and cheese.
Pour into casserole dish.
Crumble crackers.
Melt butter and mix with crackers.
Put on top of casserole.
Bake for 25 or 30 minutes at 350°.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Add toast cubes to tomatoes, salt, pepper, sugar and onion. Mix flour and milk; add to tomatoes.
Stir in cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fried mushrooms
directions: In large Ziploc bag, combine flour, salt and pepper. In shallow dish, combine eggs and water. In another shallow dish, put bread crumbs in.

title: lemon raspberry trifle
directions: In bowl, combine first 4 ingredients.
Fold in whipped topping.
Place half of cake cubes in a trifle bowl.
Sprinkle half the raspberries on top.
Top with half of lemon mixture. Repeat.
Top with raspberries.
Serves 14.

title: snickers bars
directions: Mix ingredients.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been sprayed.
Freeze.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over 1 cup All-Bran.
Set aside to cool. Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift together salt and flour.
Combine soda and buttermilk.
Alternate flour and buttermilk mixtures into sugar mixture.
Mix until smooth.
Add first mixture of All-Bran.
Blend in raisins.
Blend in 2 cups All-Bran; refrigerate.

title: apple fritters
directions: Sift together sugar, flour, salt and baking powder.
Add milk and egg.
Beat until smooth, then add chopped apples.
Drop by teaspoonfuls in hot 375° grease.
Leave in fat for 4 minutes or until brown.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper in tablespoon of butter until tender. Add sausage and brown.
Drain sausage mixture and add remaining ingredients in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Cut tops off tomatoes; save tops.
Scoop out pulp and chop.
Heat 1 tsp. oil in large nonstick skillet. Add carrot.
Add pulp and curry powder.
Cook and stir until all liquid evaporates.
Add spinach, adding more as it wilts.
Stir in raisins, nuts and salt.
Spoon into tomatoes;
replace tops. Place in baking dish, drizzle with remaining oil.
Bake 10 minutes until hot.
Serves 4.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Boil potatoes; peel and mash.
Mix well with margarine, sugar and nuts.
Form a ball around one large marshmallow, then roll in crushed cornflakes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Butter the dish.
Place asparagus on bottom of dish.
Mix soup and onions and cover the asparagus with mixture.
Bake at 350° until brown (uncovered).

title: summer dip
directions: Mix together.
Serve with potato chips or corn chips.
Makes 1 2/3 cups.

title: chicken dinner in foil
directions: Place ingredients in order given in foil and seal tightly. Place foil in shallow baking pan and bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: lemon broccoli chicken
directions: In skillet, in hot oil, cook chicken 10 minutes or until golden brown on both sides.
Spoon off fat.

title: banana spice cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except bananas.
Mash bananas, then add to batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 3 layers.
Frost with Caramel Frosting.

title: see's fudge
directions: Melt marshmallows in 1 tablespoon water in double boiler or microwave.

title: molasses tea cakes
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients all together. Add the butter or oleo. Add flavoring of your choice. Can add vanilla, cloves, nutmeg and cinnamon. Mix all ingredients together. You will have to add more flour for stiffer dough. Roll out; cut in size you want. I use a medium glass. Bake at 325°.
Do not overbake.

title: cream puffs
directions: Add butter to boiling water; heat to boiling.
Add flour all at once.
Stir over heat until smooth.
Cook until mixture leaves the sides of pan.
Don't overcook.
Cool slightly.
Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time.
Stir until smooth after adding each egg.
Beat until mixture gets glossy.
Chill (Until stiff enough to hold its shape).
Place on a baking sheet in bars or balls.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.
Cool and fill.

title: cranberry christmas mold
directions: Drain pineapple juice into measuring cup; reserve pineapple.
Add water to juice to make 1 cup.
Bring to a boil in saucepan over moderate heat.
When boiling, remove from heat, stir in gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Add cold water; chill until mixture is consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
In medium bowl combine drained pineapple and cranberry sauce; when well mixed stir into gelatin mixture.
Pour into 9 inch square pan.
Cover and chill until firm. Meanwhile, heat oven to 350°.
Place pecans and butter in a shallow pan and bake about 8 minutes, stirring occasionally, until pecans are toasted.
Cool nuts.
When gelatin mixture is firm, spread Creamy Cheese Topping over the top.
Sprinkle pecans over frosting.
Chill 3 to 4 hours until frosting is firm.
Using wet knife, cut salad into 9 squares.
With small pancake turner lift squares onto a serving plate.
Chill until serving time.
Decorate with salad greens if desired.
Makes 9 servings.

title: light caramels
directions: Boil the above 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add 1 cup of heavy whipping cream boil to 248.
Add 1 cup chopped nuts (optional).
Pour with stirring into a buttered 9 x 13 pan let set until real cool then cut & wrap.

title: fruited tea
directions: Boil 2 cups water.
Remove from heat and add tea bags and mint.
Steep for 6 minutes.
Discard tea bags and mint leaves. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight before using.

title: salt paint
directions: Spread mixture of salt and food coloring in flat pan to dry. Place in shakers (each different colors).
Sprinkle over wet paste or glue.

title: strawberry dump cake
directions: Mix and spread pie filling and pineapple in a large baking dish.
Sprinkle 1 box of yellow cake mix on top of mixture.
Chip 2 sticks of oleo and cover top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: heath bar cake
directions: No need to use mixer.
Mix sugars, brown and white, with flour. Cut in margarine with a pastry blender.
Take out 1/2 cup and put in separate bowl.
To buttermilk, add slightly beaten egg and soda. Stir this into the largest amount of dry mixture.
Mix well and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Break Heath bars using a hammer.
Stir into 1/2 cup dry mixture.
Sprinkle over batter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Freezes well.
Quick and easy.

title: low-fat chicken with spaghetti
directions: Skin and debone chicken breasts.
Roll in flour and spray with nonstick Pam, both sides. Broil until brown.
Place in baking dish and cover with spaghetti sauce. Bake at 450° until bubbly. Turn heat off.
Place cheese slices on chicken and leave in hot oven until melted. Cook spaghetti as directed on box. Serve chicken over spaghetti.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream sugar and 2 eggs; stir in sour cream and soda and add vanilla.
Stir.
Add enough flour to handle dough.
Roll 1/4-inch thick and cut out and bake at 350°.

title: black cherry salad
directions: Drain cherries, reserving liquid.
Combine cherry syrup, lemon juice and enough water to make 1 3/4 cups liquid. Heat.
Pour over jello and stir until dissolved.
Chill until partially set.
Add cherries, nuts and olives.
Pour into mold.
May also be chilled in a shallow pan and cut into squares.
Serve on crisp lettuce with mayonnaise.

title: hickory smoked stuffed trout
directions: Soak hickory chips in water at least an hour before using.

title: cheesy broccoli dip(microwave)
directions: Microwave broccoli in open packages on paper towels on High for 10 minutes; drain well.
Combine with cheese, soup and seasonings in 3-quart glass bowl.
Microwave, covered, on Medium-high until creamy, stirring occasionally.
Stir in pimento.

title: banana nut loaf
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs.
Mix flour and salt. Add flour and milk alternately.
Add vanilla.
Add soda to bananas.
Add bananas and nuts to mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat.
Add flour, salt, soda and M&M's.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mushroom pate
directions: Chop mushrooms, onion and celery and saute them in butter until tender (5 minutes); most of the liquid should be gone.
Beat other ingredients and add to mushroom mixture.
Stir until well blended.

title: sweet cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine flour and yeast.
Heat and stir milk, sugar, butter or margarine and salt until warm and butter almost melted.
Add to flour mixture plus eggs.
Beat with electric mixer on low for 30 seconds.
Scrape bowl and beat on high for 3 minutes.
Use a spoon and stir in 2 to 2 1/3 cups flour.
Knead dough on floured surface until smooth and elastic, about 3 to 5 minutes.
Shape into ball and place in slightly greased bowl.
Turn once, cover and let rise (about 1 hour).
Punch dough down.
Divide in half and let rest 10 minutes.
Roll 1/2 of dough into a 12 x 8-inch rectangle.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter.
Brush 1/2 of butter over dough.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar, 2 teaspoons cinnamon and 3/4 cup raisins (if desired). Sprinkle over dough.
Roll up from one of the long sides, seal seams, cut into 12 pieces.
Place in greased pan cover.
Let rise until nearly doubled (30 minutes).
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and cover with Powdered Sugar Icing.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and potato chips.
Place in greased oblong Pyrex casserole.
Top with cheese and chips. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: eggnog fudge
directions: Butter sides of heavy 3-quart saucepan.
In prepared pan, combine sugar, eggnog and corn syrup.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves and mixture comes to a boil.
Cook to soft ball stage (238°), stirring only as necessary.
Immediately remove from heat and cool to lukewarm (110°) without stirring.
Add the 2 tablespoons butter or margarine and the vanilla.
Beat vigorously until fudge becomes very thick and starts to lose its gloss.
Quickly stir in nuts. Spread in buttered 8 x 4 x 2-inch pan.
In glass 1-cup measure, combine chocolate pieces and remaining butter.
Set cup in saucepan filled with 1-inch water; heat until melted.
Drizzle over top of fudge; score in squares while warm.
Cut when cool and firm.
Makes 1 pound candy.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook 2/3 cup rice in 2 cups water.
Simmer 20 minutes with lid on.
Brown meat, onion, garlic, celery and pepper.
Add salt and pepper.
Add tomato puree and water.
Simmer a few minutes.
Add rice and mix well.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: stir and roll pie crust
directions: Mix ingredients.
Take half of dough and roll between 2 pieces of wax paper.
Remove 1 piece of wax paper.
Place dough into pan; remove remaining wax paper.
Makes 2 pie crusts.

title: oreo ice cream
directions: In a large bowl, beat egg yolks.
Stir in Eagle Brand milk and vanilla.
Fold in cookies and whipped cream.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, sugar, salt and 2 tablespoons cocoa. Stir in milk, oil and nuts.
Spread in 9-inch square pan, ungreased.
In a small bowl, blend brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa. Sprinkle over mixture in the pan.
Pour hot water over all.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: toffee bars
directions: Mix like pie dough with hands.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with 6 ounces chocolate chips.
Cover with bread board to melt chips.
Smooth evenly.
Cut while hot.
Cool.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Cut up chicken in serving pieces.
Place in large baking dish or pan.
Mix preserves, salad dressing and soup mix together. Pour over chicken.
Cover.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: slow cooker festive meat balls
directions: Combine beef and ham with milk, eggs, onion, pepper, bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Mix well and form into balls 2-inches or smaller in diameter.
Arrange meat balls in slow cooker.
Cover and cook 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 hours on low heat.
Turn control to high.
Stir in flour that has been dissolved in 1/4 cup water.
Add catsup and cook on high for 15 to 20 minutes or until slightly thickened. Turn heat off and stir in sour cream.
Makes 7 to 8 servings.

title: eye of round stuffed
directions: To Stuff:
Make hole in center of eye of round by twisting small knife through roast.
(Enter from both ends.)
Season hole with salt.
Stuff sausage into hole.
Heat 1 teaspoon shortening or oil and braise eye of round until it is brown on all sides.
Mix onions, bay leaves, pepper, garlic, oregano, paprika and 3 teaspoons shortening or oil.
Rub mixture over the surface of roast.
Place in a deep pan or baking dish.
Add the water and marinate overnight in the refrigerator.
Remove and roast in 325° oven, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Cover and roast for approximately 2 1/2 hours.
Remove from oven.
Carve and serve.
(Cooking time for eye of round roast is 70 minutes per pound.)

title: that stuff
directions: Cover with 1 can drained mushrooms.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours (covered).
Serve over rice, noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: ground beef and vegetable casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef and drain.
Put in a casserole dish. Add the corn, peas, onions, cheese and soup.
Mix all together. Cover with mashed potatoes.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in frozen strawberries until thawed.
Add bananas and pineapples.
Pour into 9 x 13 inch glass dish.
Put in refrigerator until set.
Add topping after jello is set.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix everything together.
Freeze. Thaw until mushy and serve. Thaw about 8 hours, 4 hours if hot weather.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix preceding ingredients together, then beat well with electric mixer until creamy.
Pour into 3 pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Frost with a good cream cheese icing or one of your choice.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, soda, cocoa and salt and sift 3 times. Take mayonnaise and mix with the hot water.
Combine liquid with dry ingredients; mix well.
Add vanilla.
Put in greased pans and bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 375°.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Melt 2/3 cup chocolate chips; set aside.
Cream
butter
and	sugar.	Add vanilla and eggs; beat well.
Add chocolate; blend.
Add flour; blend well.
Add chocolate
chips;
pour
into greased, 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.	Makes 3 dozen.

title: marzetti's french dressing
directions: Blend in electric blender.
May add onion or garlic, if desired.

title: cranberry filbert relish
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve liquid.
Measure juice and add enough water to make 2 cups.
Add sugar.
Bring to boil, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Add cranberries and cook 5 minutes.
Grate rind of one orange.
Remove segments of both oranges.
Add rind, segments, raisins and ginger to cranberry mixture.

title: long beach iced tea
directions: Fill shaker half full with ice cubes.
Add ingredients.
Shake well.
Pour into tall glass.

title: impossible buttermilk pie
directions: Grease a pie plate.
Preheat oven at 350°.
Beat all ingredients until smooth (about 1 minute) with electric mixer. Pour into pie plate.
Bake 30 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes or more.
Top with Cool Whip, fruit or ice cream.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together and roll in crushed pecans.

title: al's favorite rolls
directions: Heat water, milk, oleo, salt, and sugar to 125°.
Mix flour and yeast.
Add liquid mixture.
Stir well.
Add enough flour to knead.
Knead for approximately 10 minutes. Place in greased bowl. Let rise 1 hour.
Make into rolls and let rise 1 hour longer. Bake at 400° for approximately 18 minutes.

title: turkey or chicken salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; stir well.
Cover and chill.
Add mayonnaise, grapes, oranges and almonds to turkey mixture.
Toss well.
Serve on lettuce.
Garnish with additional orange slices and grape clusters, if desired.
Yields 6 servings.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with spoon.
Pour into long dish or make 3 layers.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Ice cake.

title: chocolate sack
directions: Thaw pastry 20 minutes.
Heat oven to 425°.
On a floured surface, roll pastry to a 14-inch square.
In center of square, place chocolate, walnuts and butter.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake 20 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve.

title: the best chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large mixer bowl, beat butter, sugars and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
In separate bowl, stir together flour, baking soda and salt. Gradually add to butter mixture.
Beat well.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet to wax paper.
Cool completely.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: steak 'n korean sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour over steak.
Marinate steak mixture for 3 to 5 hours, or longer for thicker cuts.
Refrigerate while marinating.
Remove from marinade and broil.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water.
Mix baking mix and milk.
Combine yeast with baking mix and milk.
Knead 10 times then roll to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: *Reserve remaining Cool Whip for topping.

title: angel cake
directions: Sift together powdered sugar and flour; repeat sifting twice. In a large mixer bowl, beat egg whites, cream of tartar, vanilla and 1/4 teaspoon salt at medium speed of electric mixer until soft peaks form.
Gradually add granulated sugar, about 2 tablespoons at a time.
Continue beating until stiff peaks form.
Sift about 1/4 of the flour mixture over whites; fold in lightly by hand.
If needed, transfer to a larger bowl.
Repeat, folding in remaining flour mixture by fourths.
Turn into an ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake on lowest rack in 350° oven for about 40 minutes or until done.
Invert cake in pan; cool completely.
Loosen cake from pan; remove.
Serves 12.

title: uncooked oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix white sugar, margarine and milk in saucepan. Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat. Add remaining ingredients. Stir together, then drop by tablespoonfuls on waxed paper and let cool.

title: fungus among-us cutlets(cheese and mushroom chops)
directions: Add own seasonings or sprinkle with Mrs.
Dash as cooking. Mix all ingredients except butter.
Take 1/4 to 1/3 cup mix; brown in butter on both sides.
If using measuring cup, flatten mixture to 3/4-inch thick with fork.
Should be crisp outside, moist inside.
Use as is or make a sandwich.
Can be frozen.
Serves 4.

title: avocado salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.
Serve on lettuce bed.

title: broccoli-onion pilaf
directions: In a large nonstick skillet over medium-low heat, cook the onion, garlic and red pepper flakes in the oil until the onion is golden, 10 to 20 minutes.
Stir in the vinegar, black pepper, broccoli and millet or rice.
Toss to combine and sprinkle with the Parmesan and carrots.
Serves 8.

title: hot fruit
directions: Drain all the fruit and save the juice, except the juice of the cherries.
Arrange the fruit in a shallow casserole dish.
Combine 1 3/4 cups of the fruit juice, cornstarch, butter, brown sugar and cooking sherry.
Cook over medium-low heat until the mixture thickens.
Pour mixture over the fruit.

title: pie crust
directions: Use pastry blender to mix flour and Crisco.
Add cold water. Use wooden spatula until forms ball.
Turn out on biscuit board and work with it, then roll out.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: trudy's apple strudel(this is an old vienna recipe!)
directions: Peel and core all apples; slice on a grater.
Put aside.
Get a cookie sheet out for later.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Heat margarine over low heat until melted.
Blend in flour, onion, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth and bubbly; remove from heat.
Stir in broth and milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in chicken and frozen vegetables.
Pour filling into pie crust.
Cook in 350° oven until crust is done (approximately 1 hour).

title: everybody's chocolate soda
directions: Mix one scoop of ice cream with the chocolate sauce in bottom of tall glass.
Fill with soda or cola to 1 inch from the top. Stir gently and add final scoop of ice cream.

title: apple pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and place into unbaked pie shell. cover with top pastry.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cauliflower and broccoli mix
directions: Cut cauliflower and broccoli up.
Cook bacon until crisp, then crumble up into small pieces.
Add raisins and sugar.
Toss all ingredients together until covered with dressing.
Best if made the night before and put in the refrigerator.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix together brown sugar and cinnamon.
Melt butter.
Roll biscuits in butter, then in mixture.
Arrange and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: old-fashioned buttermilk cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; cream together until light and fluffy. Add vanilla and eggs; blend well.
Stir soda into buttermilk and add to creamed mixture alternately with flour.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bounce pans to remove air bubbles.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: light pasta salad
directions: Blend mayonnaise and Ranch dressing in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Chill.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: cavatini
directions: Mix everything together.
Pour in casserole and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: frankwiches
directions: Combine uncooked hot dog slices, cheese, mustard and relish in bowl.
Add sugar and enough catsup to coat hot dogs well.
Spoon into buns and wrap individually in foil.
Freeze if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: classic chocolate sauce
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add sugar, cocoa and milk, half at a time, stirring constantly.
Add salt.
Stir until mixture just begins to boil.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Makes 3 to 4 cups.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Beat eggs.
Add the remaining ingredients, including the sausage.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well; spread in baking dish.
Cover with crushed potato chips or buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: pre-civil war pound cake
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat yolks until thick.
Add sugar.
After sifting three times, cream butter and flour, then add mixture of sugar, eggs and flavoring.
Beat well.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into former mixture.
Bake in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: rice pudding
directions: Bring rice, water and salt to boil.
Simmer until rice is done, about 15 minutes.
Take off heat and stir in milk and raisins.
Beat eggs and gradually add to rice mixture.
Stir briskly.
Return to heat and cook until coats spoon.
Add rest of ingredients.

title: sex cake
directions: Cook and punch holes in top of cake with wooden spoon handle. Boil pineapple and sugar together until you get a syrup.
Pour over cake while both are hot.
Let cool; put a layer of sliced bananas on top of cake.
Make a banana pudding and spread over top of bananas and let cool.
Top with whipped topping and crushed pineapple, drained, and mixed with nuts.

title: creamy chicken and rice skillet dinner
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet.
Add chicken and cook 7 minutes until lightly browned.
Add 1 3/4 cups water and the rice mix. Stir to mix.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes, turning chicken and stirring rice occasionally, until rice is almost tender.
Add vegetables. Increase heat and cook, uncovered, about 7 minutes, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are tender and chicken is cooked through.
Stir in cheese.
Serves 4.

title: magic topping
directions: Cook, stirring, until sugar melts.
Spread on top of warm cake.
Return to oven and bake for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: cheese pie
directions: Cream cheese, sugar and egg yolks together.
Add vanilla and cornstarch.
Add milk. Stir.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour in two pie crusts.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes. Turn down to 350° for 30 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Sprinkle with cinnamon or nutmeg.

title: ham rolls
directions: Place 1 or 2 asparagus spears on a slice of ham.
Top with slice of cheese.
Roll up and secure with toothpick.
Place on ovenproof platter and put into 350° oven until cheese melts. Serve hot or cold.

title: ham and bean soup
directions: Fry bacon in heavy skillet.
Drain and crumble.
Keep drippings for later use.
Cover beans with water in a heavy pot. Bring to boil.
Cook until beans are tender, approximately 2 1/2 hours.
Add onion, seasoning, ham, corn and bacon.
Simmer for 1 hour.
In a small skillet, add bacon drippings and flour, stir until lightly browned.
Add 1 1/2 cups water to make a gravy, stirring frequently.
Pour into soup and simmer for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: german sauer klopps (sour meat balls)
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients well and form into 1 1/2-inch meat balls.
Bring water, onion, spices and 1/4 teaspoon of salt to a boil.
Add meat balls and simmer until done, about 25 minutes. Remove meat balls and thicken broth with flour paste.
Bring to a boil.
Add sour cream and heat through, but do not boil.
Return meat balls to gravy and heat.
Serve with boiled potatoes.

title: creamy lemon icing(lemon flavoring enhances this icing.)
directions: In a small bowl, mix sugar and egg thoroughly.
In a saucepan, boil, for one minute, lemon juice and powdered sugar together, stirring often.
Add this mixture to sugar and egg mixture, and blend well.
Add oleo and rind; beat until creamy.
Spread on cake and sprinkle with coconut, if desired.

title: fudge like grandma never thought about
directions: Combine sugar, sour cream, milk, oleo, Karo and salt in heavy saucepan.
Stir over moderate heat until sugar is dissolved and mixture comes to a boil.
Cook to soft ball stage (9 to 10 minutes at 238°).
Remove from heat; allow to cool to 110°, approximately 1 hour.
Add vanilla; beat until it begins to lose its gloss.
Add pecans and cherries (if used).
Pour into oiled dish.
When firm, cut into squares.
Store in closed container.
Keeps 3 to 4 weeks in refrigerator.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream
sugars,
oleo
and eggs and beat.
Add all other ingredients.
Put
in
balls
the
size
of walnuts on greased sheet.
Press
with
bottom of glass dipped in water and sugar and flatten out.
I
usually
only dip glass in water once but have to dip in sugar after each one.
Bake at 350° until done. Do not get too brown.
Just barely done.
Makes a lot.

title: pineapple bars
directions: Cook together the sugar, cornstarch and crushed pineapple until thick and clear; set aside to cool.
Mix together the flour, salt, brown sugar, rolled oats and shortening until crumbly. Spread 1/2 mixture in well-greased baking dish, then spread pineapple mixture with remainder of crumb mixture.
Press down. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix together pudding (dry), pineapple and Cool Whip thoroughly; then add marshmallows.
Put in square Pyrex pan, cover with chopped nuts. Refrigerate.

title: mushroom patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
If mixture is too soft, add bread crumbs or flour to stiffen.
Shape into patties and fry.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix together sugar and cornstarch.
Add 7-Up.
Cook and stir until clear.
Add strawberry Jell-O; cook until thick.
Cool to room temperature.
Add sliced strawberries.
Pour into prepared pie shell.
Refrigerate.
Serve with Cool Whip.
Good with fresh peaches and peach Jell-O also.
Makes 1 (8 to 9-inch) pie.

title: sunday chicken legs
directions: Wash and dry chicken legs.
Mix flour, salt and seasoned salt. Roll chicken pieces in flour mixture, then in beaten eggs, then in flour again.
Place chicken in a buttered shallow baking dish. Sprinkle with butter.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 25 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with teriyaki sauce and bake another 5 to 10 minutes longer or until chicken is done.

title: beef tenderloin marinade
directions: Mix together and pour over beef to marinate overnight or 8 hours.
Grill or bake in oven.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Allow frozen strawberries to thaw.
Drain juice and divide berries evenly, half for cake and half for icing.
Save 1 tablespoon juice for icing.
Add water to remaining juice to make 1/2 cup.
Put all ingredients in mixing bowl and beat until well mixed.
Bake in 3 layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Serve on snack crackers.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix together the Cool Whip and sour cream thoroughly.
Add orange Jell-O; mix until blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill in refrigerator about 1 hour before serving.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat milk, pudding and orange juice; stir in sour cream. Serve with pineapple, apple slices, banana slices and/or mandarin oranges.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Cook devil's food cake mix as directed on package.
While hot, mix Hershey's chocolate chips, sugar, butter and milk in pot. Melt and let boil 3 minutes.
Pour onto cake.

title: mexican layer dip
directions: Spread bean dip in bottom of 13 X 9 inch pan. Mash avocados with lemon juice, adding salt if desired. Spread evenly over bean dip. Combine sour cream with taco mix, blend well. Spread over avocado. Sprinkle cheese, tomatoes and black olives on top. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except tomato sauce.
Use enough condensed milk to make loaf easy to handle.
Pour in loaf pan and top with tomato sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sunflower seed loaf
directions: Simmer bulgur wheat for 15 minutes in 2 cups of water and 4 tablespoons of soy sauce.
While bulgur is simmering, whiz sunflower seeds, celery salt and 2 cups of water.
Put sunflower seed mixture in a bowl with 2 cups of oats and stir; set aside. Next, saute finely chopped onion and garlic with sage, oil and marjoram.
Combine all ingredients and place in a greased casserole dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Yields 8 to 9 servings.

title: savory tomato soup
directions: Fry bacon and crumble.
Saute onions and celery in butter. Add flour to sauteed onions and celery.
Place tomatoes, water and chicken bouillon in saucepan and boil.
Add sauteed onions and celery to boiling tomatoes.
Add crumbled bacon.
Cook on low or medium heat for 30 to 60 minutes.

title: tropical punch
directions: Blend all together and strain.
Freeze in ice trays.
Serve 1 large bottle of 7-Up or ginger ale to one tray of ice to make punch.

title: carrot bars
directions: Beat whole eggs and soda together.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake in cookie sheet at 350°.

title: easy punch
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the 7-Up.
Just before serving, add 7-Up.
Makes about 40 cups.
Pour over crushed ice. Use different flavors of Kool-Aid for different occasions.

title: hamburger dish
directions: Layer meat, noodles, onion, celery and soup, using raw meat and uncooked noodles.
Add 1 can of water over the top.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in the eggs and sour cream.
Add all the corn and liquid from corn.
After all ingredients are well mixed, fold in the corn muffin mix.
Bake at 350° until brown and puffy (approximately 25 minutes).
Can be prepared ahead of time.

title: chicken green bean casserole
directions: Combine the mushroom soup, milk and salt and stir until blended.
Fold in French beans, chicken, chop suey vegetables, onion, Cheddar cheese and mushrooms.
Spoon mixture into baking dish (12 x 7 1/2 x 2 inches) and bake 45 minutes in 350°
oven or until beans are tender.
Top with French onions and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: hot apple cider(serves 25)
directions: Heat cider, spices and sugar to boiling.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Put the spices in a tea ball and hang over side of pan. I usually put in a crock-pot to keep warm.
